1
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:21,000


2
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:33,000


3
00:00:53,716 --> 00:01:00,262


4
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:15,210


5
00:01:41,039 --> 00:01:44,664


6
00:01:52,668 --> 00:01:55,664
I'm dying of thirst over here. C'mon, come on!

7
00:01:56,564 --> 00:01:57,832
Here you are.

8
00:02:02,664 --> 00:02:04,638
- Watch it!  - Sorry, darling.

9
00:02:06,156 --> 00:02:07,941
- Here you are.  - Ah, thank you.

10
00:02:46,854 --> 00:02:48,447
Mind if I join you?

11
00:02:48,747 --> 00:02:49,847
I'll have the same.

12
00:02:56,205 --> 00:03:01,805
I should introduce myself. My name is Gandalf, Gandalf the Grey.

13
00:03:01,805 --> 00:03:03,605
I know who you are.

14
00:03:03,905 --> 00:03:08,005
Well, now! This is a fine chance.

15
00:03:09,405 --> 00:03:13,605
What brings Thorin Oakenshield to Bree?

16
00:03:16,005 --> 00:03:21,705
I received word, that my father has been seen wandering the wilds near Dunland.

17
00:03:23,105 --> 00:03:26,805
I went looking, found no sign of him.

18
00:03:27,205 --> 00:03:32,605
Thorin, It has been a long time since anything but rumour was heard of Thrain.

19
00:03:32,605 --> 00:03:36,605
He still lives, I am sure of it.

20
00:03:40,405 --> 00:03:43,955
My father came to see you before he went missing.

21
00:03:43,955 --> 00:03:45,505
What did you say to him?

22
00:03:45,505 --> 00:03:48,605
I urged him to march upon Erebor.

23
00:03:48,605 --> 00:03:51,305
To run the seven armies of the dwarves.

24
00:03:51,305 --> 00:03:55,505
To destroy the dragon and take back the Lonely Mountain.

25
00:03:55,505 --> 00:03:57,552
And I would say the same to you,

26
00:03:57,752 --> 00:04:00,859
take back your homeland.

27
00:04:04,405 --> 00:04:07,605
This is no chance meeting, is it, Gandalf?

28
00:04:08,805 --> 00:04:12,400
No. It is not.

29
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:17,953
The Lonely Mountain troubles me, Thorin. That dragon has sat there long enough.

30
00:04:17,953 --> 00:04:23,037
Sooner or later, darker minds will turn towards Erebor.

31
00:04:23,037 --> 00:04:27,944
I ran into some unsavory characters, whilst travelling along the Greenway.

32
00:04:28,244 --> 00:04:30,754
They mistook me for a vagabond.

33
00:04:30,754 --> 00:04:32,520
I imagine they regretted that.

34
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:35,604
One of them was carrying a message.

35
00:04:37,505 --> 00:04:39,521
It is Black Speech.

36
00:04:42,287 --> 00:04:43,719
A promise of payment.

37
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,794
For what?

38
00:04:47,164 --> 00:04:48,798
Your head.

39
00:04:50,605 --> 00:04:52,705
Someone wants you dead.

40
00:04:53,805 --> 00:04:59,505
Thorin, you could wait no longer. You are the heir to the throne of Durin.

41
00:04:59,505 --> 00:05:03,976
Unite the armies of the dwarves. Together, you have the might and power...

42
00:05:03,976 --> 00:05:05,736
to retake Erebor.

43
00:05:06,505 --> 00:05:08,854
Summon a meeting of the seven dwarf families. 

44
00:05:08,854 --> 00:05:10,754
Demand they stand by their oaths.

45
00:05:10,954 --> 00:05:14,827
The seven armies swore that oath to the one who wields the King's jewel...

46
00:05:14,827 --> 00:05:16,027
the Arkenstone.

47
00:05:16,763 --> 00:05:18,525
It is the only thing that would unite them.

48
00:05:18,525 --> 00:05:22,244
And in case you've forgotten, that jewel was stolen by Smaug.

49
00:05:26,557 --> 00:05:29,705
What if, I were to help you reclaim it?

50
00:05:30,905 --> 00:05:32,160
How?

51
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:35,547
The Arkenstone lies half a world away.

52
00:05:35,547 --> 00:05:38,005
Buried beneath the feet of a fire breathing dragon.

53
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:43,805
Yes, it does. Which is why we are going to need a burglar.

54
00:05:46,291 --> 00:05:48,631


55
00:06:33,435 --> 00:06:39,005


56
00:06:44,005 --> 00:06:46,405
- How close is the pack?  - Too close.

57
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:49,424
A couple of leagues, no more. But that's not the worst of it.

58
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:49,424


59
00:06:49,424 --> 00:06:51,902
- Have the Orcs picked up our scent?  - Not yet, but they will do.

60
00:06:51,902 --> 00:06:53,002
We have another problem.

61
00:06:53,002 --> 00:06:55,095
Did they see you? They saw you?

62
00:06:55,095 --> 00:06:56,295
No, that's not it.

63
00:06:56,495 --> 00:06:59,149
Good, what did I tell you? Quite as a mouse.

64
00:06:59,605 --> 00:07:01,860
- Excellent burglar material!  - Will you listen.

65
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:04,013
Will you just listen?

66
00:07:04,013 --> 00:07:07,085
I'm trying to tell you, there is something else out there.

67
00:07:08,535 --> 00:07:12,415
What form did it take... Like a bear?

68
00:07:12,726 --> 00:07:16,799
Ye... yes, yes. But, bigger, much bigger!

69
00:07:17,655 --> 00:07:19,805
You knew about this beast?

70
00:07:21,097 --> 00:07:24,205
- I say we double back.  - And be run down by a pack of Orcs?

71
00:07:24,805 --> 00:07:26,627
There is a house.

72
00:07:28,224 --> 00:07:32,462
It's not far from here, where we might take refuge.

73
00:07:32,462 --> 00:07:35,487
Whose house, a friend or a foe?

74
00:07:35,687 --> 00:07:37,763
Neither 'en.

75
00:07:38,605 --> 00:07:42,805
He will help us... or he will kill us.

76
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:45,605
What choice do we have?

77
00:07:47,755 --> 00:07:48,905
None.

78
00:07:56,255 --> 00:07:57,905
Run!

79
00:07:58,455 --> 00:07:59,905
<b><i>Abgurid!</i></b>

80
00:08:07,705 --> 00:08:09,805
This way, quickly!

81
00:08:09,956 --> 00:08:11,138
Run!

82
00:08:19,605 --> 00:08:20,805
In the house.

83
00:08:22,805 --> 00:08:24,705
Run!

84
00:08:31,905 --> 00:08:33,605
Come on, get inside!

85
00:08:46,705 --> 00:08:48,212
Open the door!

86
00:08:48,412 --> 00:08:49,412
Quickly!

87
00:09:00,405 --> 00:09:01,805
Push!

88
00:09:04,905 --> 00:09:06,805
Come on, lads!

89
00:09:11,505 --> 00:09:13,205
What is that?

90
00:09:13,605 --> 00:09:15,805
That is our host.

91
00:09:19,905 --> 00:09:22,805
His name is Beorn.

92
00:09:23,955 --> 00:09:26,705
And he is a skin-changer.

93
00:09:27,905 --> 00:09:30,572
Sometimes, he is a huge black bear.

94
00:09:30,572 --> 00:09:32,837
Sometimes, he is a great strong man.

95
00:09:33,037 --> 00:09:37,022
The bear is unpredictable. But the man can be reasoned with.

96
00:09:37,022 --> 00:09:41,291
However, he's not over fond of Dwarves.

97
00:09:44,105 --> 00:09:45,076
He is leaving.

98
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:46,676
Come away from there!

99
00:09:47,605 --> 00:09:49,988
It's not natural. None of it.

100
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:53,605
It's obvious, he's under some dark spell.

101
00:09:53,605 --> 00:09:55,005
Don't be a fool.

102
00:09:55,205 --> 00:09:57,438
He is under no enchantment but his own.

103
00:09:57,638 --> 00:09:58,638
Alright, now!

104
00:09:58,838 --> 00:10:01,275
Get some sleep, all of you.

105
00:10:01,275 --> 00:10:03,744
You will be safe here, tonight.

106
00:10:07,521 --> 00:10:09,605
I hope.

107
00:10:25,721 --> 00:10:27,455


108
00:10:28,421 --> 00:10:31,005


109
00:10:32,121 --> 00:10:33,355


110
00:10:36,071 --> 00:10:38,205


111
00:10:44,721 --> 00:10:47,705


112
00:10:59,421 --> 00:11:02,235


113
00:11:03,121 --> 00:11:06,655


114
00:11:59,561 --> 00:12:02,755
<b><i>Ash nazg durbatuluk</i></b>

115
00:12:03,421 --> 00:12:06,655
<b><i>Ash nazg gimbatul</i></b>

116
00:12:07,391 --> 00:12:11,155
<b><i>Ash nazg thrakatuluk</i></b>

117
00:12:12,121 --> 00:12:15,655
<b><i>Agh burzum-ishi krimpatul</i></b>

118
00:12:49,954 --> 00:12:52,953


119
00:12:53,315 --> 00:12:56,037


120
00:12:56,341 --> 00:12:58,664


121
00:12:59,307 --> 00:13:01,726


122
00:13:04,489 --> 00:13:08,350


123
00:13:08,578 --> 00:13:10,491


124
00:13:11,657 --> 00:13:13,491


125
00:13:18,389 --> 00:13:20,569


126
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:26,427


127
00:13:40,284 --> 00:13:42,512


128
00:13:43,936 --> 00:13:47,417


129
00:14:50,805 --> 00:14:54,605
So, you are the one they call Oakenshield?

130
00:14:55,205 --> 00:14:56,544
Tell me,

131
00:14:56,744 --> 00:15:00,849
why is Azog the Defiler hunting you?

132
00:15:01,049 --> 00:15:04,228
You know of Azog, how?

133
00:15:04,228 --> 00:15:07,648
My people were the first to live in the mountains,

134
00:15:08,705 --> 00:15:11,605
before the Orcs came down from the north.

135
00:15:11,605 --> 00:15:14,705
The Defiler killed most of my family.

136
00:15:15,605 --> 00:15:17,912
But some he enslaved.

137
00:15:18,112 --> 00:15:22,693
Not for work, you understand? But for sport.

138
00:15:23,705 --> 00:15:28,805
Caging skin changers and torturing them seemed to amuse him.

139
00:15:29,905 --> 00:15:32,705
There are others like you?

140
00:15:33,605 --> 00:15:35,905
Once there were many.

141
00:15:36,405 --> 00:15:37,705
And now?

142
00:15:38,605 --> 00:15:41,805
Now, there's only one.

143
00:15:42,805 --> 00:15:47,605
You need to reach the mountain before the last days of autumn.

144
00:15:47,705 --> 00:15:50,662
Before Durin's Day falls, yes.

145
00:15:50,862 --> 00:15:52,852
You are running out of time.

146
00:15:52,852 --> 00:15:55,448
Which is why we must go through Mirkwood.

147
00:15:55,448 --> 00:15:58,276
A darkness lies upon that forest.

148
00:15:58,405 --> 00:16:01,705
Foul things creep beneath those trees.

149
00:16:02,305 --> 00:16:07,705
There is an alliance between the Orcs of Moria and the Necromancer in Dol Guldur.

150
00:16:08,705 --> 00:16:12,205
I will not venture there, except in great need.

151
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:16,316
We will take the Elven road. Their path is still safe.

152
00:16:16,316 --> 00:16:17,646
Safe?

153
00:16:17,846 --> 00:16:21,096
The Wood Elves of Mirkwood are not like their kin.

154
00:16:21,096 --> 00:16:24,506
They are less wise and more dangerous.

155
00:16:25,705 --> 00:16:27,705
But it matters not.

156
00:16:29,605 --> 00:16:30,605
What do you mean?

157
00:16:30,705 --> 00:16:33,922
These lands are crawling with Orcs.

158
00:16:34,122 --> 00:16:37,070
Their numbers are growing.

159
00:16:37,270 --> 00:16:42,605
And you are on foot. You will never reach the forest alive.

160
00:16:46,905 --> 00:16:49,705
I don't like Dwarves.

161
00:16:50,705 --> 00:16:52,415
They are greedy...

162
00:16:52,615 --> 00:16:54,847
and blind.

163
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:59,647
Blind to the lives of those they deem less than their own.

164
00:17:06,705 --> 00:17:09,205
But Orcs, I hate more.

165
00:17:10,705 --> 00:17:12,805
What do you need?

166
00:17:17,705 --> 00:17:20,605
Go now, while you have the light.

167
00:17:20,805 --> 00:17:24,605
Your hunters are not far behind.

168
00:17:47,705 --> 00:17:49,805
The Elven Gate.

169
00:17:50,705 --> 00:17:53,805
Here lies our path through Mirkwood.

170
00:17:53,905 --> 00:17:55,929
No sign of the Orcs.

171
00:17:56,129 --> 00:17:58,185
We have luck on our side.

172
00:18:04,705 --> 00:18:09,605
Set the ponies loose, let them return to their master.

173
00:18:11,705 --> 00:18:16,189
This forest... feels sick.

174
00:18:16,389 --> 00:18:19,218
As if a disease lies upon it.

175
00:18:20,805 --> 00:18:22,905
Is there no way around?

176
00:18:22,905 --> 00:18:27,605
Not unless we go 200 miles north or twice that distance...

177
00:18:28,705 --> 00:18:31,805
south.

178
00:18:55,905 --> 00:18:59,705
Something moves in the shadows, unseen.

179
00:19:00,705 --> 00:19:03,505
Hidden from outside.

180
00:19:04,105 --> 00:19:06,805
Everyday it grows in strength.

181
00:19:08,605 --> 00:19:10,605
Beware the Necromancer.

182
00:19:11,605 --> 00:19:14,605
He's not what he seems.

183
00:19:17,805 --> 00:19:21,605
If our enemy has returned, we must know.

184
00:19:22,705 --> 00:19:25,605
Go to the tombs in the mountains.

185
00:19:26,605 --> 00:19:29,605
The High Fells.

186
00:19:32,605 --> 00:19:33,805
So be it.

187
00:19:38,005 --> 00:19:40,605
Not my horse, I need it.

188
00:19:41,805 --> 00:19:43,620
You're not leaving us?

189
00:19:43,620 --> 00:19:45,320
I would not do this unless I had to.

190
00:19:51,805 --> 00:19:54,805
You've changed, Bilbo Baggins.

191
00:19:56,705 --> 00:20:00,205
You're not the same hobbit as the one left the Shire.

192
00:20:02,605 --> 00:20:03,805
I was going to tell you...

193
00:20:07,705 --> 00:20:13,855
I found something in the goblin tunnels.

194
00:20:13,855 --> 00:20:16,105
Found what?

195
00:20:20,405 --> 00:20:21,705
What did you find?

196
00:20:25,385 --> 00:20:27,805
My courage.

197
00:20:29,305 --> 00:20:32,805
Good. That's good.

198
00:20:33,905 --> 00:20:36,374
You will need it.

199
00:20:36,574 --> 00:20:40,946
I will be waiting for you at the overlook, before the slopes of Erebor.

200
00:20:41,146 --> 00:20:43,703
Heed the map and keep it safe!

201
00:20:43,903 --> 00:20:46,805
Do not enter that mountain without me.

202
00:20:52,169 --> 00:20:55,739
This is not the Greenwood alone.

203
00:20:56,083 --> 00:20:59,557
The very air of the forest is heavy, with illusion.

204
00:20:59,757 --> 00:21:01,308
It will seek to enter your mind...

205
00:21:01,508 --> 00:21:04,068
- and lead you astray.  - Lead us astray?

206
00:21:04,268 --> 00:21:06,004
What does that mean?

207
00:21:06,521 --> 00:21:08,233
You must stay on the path!

208
00:21:08,233 --> 00:21:11,480
Do not leave it. If you do...

209
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:13,688
you'll never find it again.

210
00:21:14,948 --> 00:21:17,849
No matter what may come, stay on the path!

211
00:21:17,849 --> 00:21:21,931
Come on! We must reach the mountain, before the sun sets on Durin's Day.

212
00:21:22,675 --> 00:21:25,177
It's our one chance to find the hidden door.

213
00:21:35,872 --> 00:21:37,454
The path turns this way.

214
00:22:03,718 --> 00:22:04,949
This way.

215
00:22:13,553 --> 00:22:15,110
Air...

216
00:22:15,110 --> 00:22:16,210
I need air.

217
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:19,290
My head... It's spinning!

218
00:22:19,290 --> 00:22:21,490
- What's happening?  - Keep moving.

219
00:22:21,990 --> 00:22:26,180
Nori, why have we stopped?

220
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:28,590
The path, it's disappeared!

221
00:22:29,141 --> 00:22:32,843
- What's going on?  - We've lost the path!

222
00:22:33,055 --> 00:22:34,477
Find it!

223
00:22:34,677 --> 00:22:37,449
All of you, look. Look for the path!

224
00:22:46,701 --> 00:22:49,338
I don't remember, this place is a mess.

225
00:22:49,338 --> 00:22:51,052
None of it is familiar.

226
00:22:51,286 --> 00:22:53,186
It's got to be here.

227
00:22:53,503 --> 00:22:55,497
What hour is it?

228
00:22:55,497 --> 00:22:58,612
I don't know, I don't even know what day it is.

229
00:22:59,242 --> 00:23:03,283
Is there no end to this accursed place!

230
00:23:45,874 --> 00:23:48,553
Look, a tobacco pouch.

231
00:23:48,753 --> 00:23:51,801
There's dwarves in these woods!

232
00:23:52,001 --> 00:23:53,982
Dwarves from the Blue Mountain, no less.

233
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:57,473
- This is exactly the same as mine!  - Because it is yours.

234
00:23:57,651 --> 00:24:01,059
Do you understand? We're going around in circles, we are lost.

235
00:24:01,059 --> 00:24:03,052
We are not lost. We keep heading east.

236
00:24:03,052 --> 00:24:05,987
But which way is the east? We've lost the sun!

237
00:24:08,693 --> 00:24:10,413
The sun.

238
00:24:10,613 --> 00:24:14,433
We have to find... the sun.

239
00:24:15,365 --> 00:24:16,568
Up there.

240
00:24:16,965 --> 00:24:17,868
We need to...

241
00:24:27,083 --> 00:24:29,888
Enough! Quiet! All of you.

242
00:24:31,532 --> 00:24:33,472
We are being watched.

243
00:25:21,005 --> 00:25:23,185
I can... see a lake!

244
00:25:24,483 --> 00:25:26,361
And the... river.

245
00:25:28,094 --> 00:25:29,649
And the Lonely Mountain.

246
00:25:29,849 --> 00:25:32,145
We are almost there!

247
00:25:34,084 --> 00:25:35,524
Can you hear me?

248
00:25:36,759 --> 00:25:38,764
I know which way to go!

249
00:25:42,246 --> 00:25:43,212
Hello?!

250
00:25:52,727 --> 00:25:54,418
Hello.

251
00:27:48,890 --> 00:27:52,493
<i>Kill them. Kill them! Eat them now while all their blood is running.</i>

252
00:27:52,493 --> 00:27:54,193
<i>Their hide is tough.</i>

253
00:27:54,237 --> 00:27:57,041
<i>This could be smushy inside.</i>

254
00:27:58,798 --> 00:28:00,310
<i>Finish it off.</i>

255
00:28:00,510 --> 00:28:03,923
<i>Who needs it alive... Let us kill him. Kill him, kill him, now!</i>

256
00:28:03,923 --> 00:28:06,675
<i>Let us feast... feast... feast.</i>

257
00:28:06,948 --> 00:28:10,158
<i>Feast... feast!</i>

258
00:28:20,948 --> 00:28:21,858
<i>What is it?</i>

259
00:28:30,099 --> 00:28:32,886
<i>Fat and juicy!</i>

260
00:28:35,351 --> 00:28:38,385
<i>Just a little taste!</i>

261
00:28:48,592 --> 00:28:50,964
<i>Curse it! Where is it? Where is it?!</i>

262
00:28:52,539 --> 00:28:54,170
Here!

263
00:28:54,370 --> 00:28:58,113
<i>It stings... Stings!</i>

264
00:29:03,406 --> 00:29:04,724
Sting.

265
00:29:05,517 --> 00:29:06,817
That's a good name.

266
00:29:08,777 --> 00:29:09,940
Sting.

267
00:29:31,456 --> 00:29:32,556
Where is Bilbo?

268
00:29:33,125 --> 00:29:34,181
I'm up here!

269
00:30:15,211 --> 00:30:16,903
Where is it? Where's it?

270
00:30:17,189 --> 00:30:19,542
Come on! Where is it?

271
00:30:44,223 --> 00:30:45,602
Thorin!

272
00:30:55,349 --> 00:30:56,467
Kili!

273
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:21,452
Mine!

274
00:31:57,266 --> 00:31:58,753
Come on, keep up!

275
00:31:59,445 --> 00:32:00,535
We are clear!

276
00:32:21,549 --> 00:32:23,687
Do not think I won't kill you, Dwarf.

277
00:32:24,359 --> 00:32:26,013
It would be my pleasure.

278
00:32:31,455 --> 00:32:32,661
Kili!

279
00:32:50,593 --> 00:32:51,863
Throw me a dagger!

280
00:32:52,487 --> 00:32:53,477
Quick!

281
00:32:53,777 --> 00:32:57,878
If you think I'm giving you a weapon, Dwarf, you are mistaken.

282
00:33:03,251 --> 00:33:04,486
Search them!

283
00:33:10,985 --> 00:33:12,558
Hey, give it back! That's private!

284
00:33:12,758 --> 00:33:14,138
Who's this?

285
00:33:14,338 --> 00:33:17,156
- Your brother?  - That is my wife!

286
00:33:17,617 --> 00:33:21,174
And, what is this horrid creature? A Goblin Mutant?

287
00:33:21,174 --> 00:33:23,519
That's my wee lad, Gimli!

288
00:33:30,477 --> 00:33:31,452


289
00:33:32,154 --> 00:33:34,350


290
00:33:35,685 --> 00:33:37,397


291
00:33:44,838 --> 00:33:48,020


292
00:33:49,623 --> 00:33:52,993


293
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:56,483
Where did you get this?

294
00:33:56,683 --> 00:33:58,853
It was given to me.

295
00:34:01,313 --> 00:34:03,075
Not just a thief...

296
00:34:03,075 --> 00:34:04,835
but a liar as well.

297
00:34:05,109 --> 00:34:06,601
<i>Take them away!</i>

298
00:34:09,211 --> 00:34:10,923
Thorin, Where is Bilbo?

299
00:34:24,876 --> 00:34:26,020


300
00:35:15,402 --> 00:35:16,981
This is not the end of it!

301
00:35:17,877 --> 00:35:18,873
Do you hear me?!

302
00:35:19,246 --> 00:35:20,674
Let us out of here!

303
00:35:28,887 --> 00:35:31,690
Aren't you going to search me?

304
00:35:31,728 --> 00:35:33,722
I could have anything down my trousers?

305
00:35:35,038 --> 00:35:37,010
Or, nothing.

306
00:35:45,263 --> 00:35:48,476


307
00:35:48,476 --> 00:35:50,504


308
00:35:50,904 --> 00:35:54,321


309
00:35:55,207 --> 00:35:56,137


310
00:35:56,486 --> 00:35:58,104


311
00:35:59,375 --> 00:36:01,004


312
00:36:12,020 --> 00:36:13,936
- Arhhg... again!  - Leave it!

313
00:36:14,136 --> 00:36:15,136
There is no way out!

314
00:36:15,665 --> 00:36:20,769
This is no Orc dungeon. These are the Halls of the Woodland realm.

315
00:36:21,047 --> 00:36:25,220
No one leaves here, but, by the King's consent.

316
00:36:29,073 --> 00:36:33,179
Some may imagine that a noble quest is at hand.

317
00:36:33,419 --> 00:36:38,390
A quest to reclaim a homeland and slay a dragon.

318
00:36:39,706 --> 00:36:44,152
I myself, suspect a more prosaic motive.

319
00:36:44,487 --> 00:36:47,327
Attempted burglary...

320
00:36:47,363 --> 00:36:50,167
or something of that ilk.

321
00:36:52,414 --> 00:36:54,662
You have found a way in?

322
00:36:54,862 --> 00:36:59,315
You seek that which would bestow upon you the right to rule.

323
00:36:59,768 --> 00:37:01,831
A King's Jewel.

324
00:37:01,875 --> 00:37:05,181
The Arkenstone.

325
00:37:05,887 --> 00:37:08,919
It is precious to you, beyond measure.

326
00:37:10,668 --> 00:37:13,370
I understand that.

327
00:37:13,410 --> 00:37:16,784
There are gems in the mountain that I too desire.

328
00:37:18,191 --> 00:37:22,696
White gems, a pure starlight.

329
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:25,910
I offer you my help.

330
00:37:27,922 --> 00:37:29,341
I am listening.

331
00:37:29,541 --> 00:37:31,325
I will let you go.

332
00:37:31,525 --> 00:37:35,378
If you but return what is mine.

333
00:37:38,113 --> 00:37:39,727
A favour, for a favour.

334
00:37:39,728 --> 00:37:41,543
You have my word.

335
00:37:42,138 --> 00:37:44,640
One King to another.

336
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:52,244
I would not trust, Thranduil.

337
00:37:52,244 --> 00:37:57,585
The great king, to only his word. Till the end of all days be upon us.

338
00:37:58,451 --> 00:38:00,047
You!

339
00:38:00,089 --> 00:38:02,085
Lack all honour!

340
00:38:02,564 --> 00:38:07,284
I've seen how you treat your friends. We came to you once...

341
00:38:07,284 --> 00:38:11,460
Starving, homeless, seeking your help.

342
00:38:11,660 --> 00:38:14,185
But you turned your back!

343
00:38:14,434 --> 00:38:17,499
You, turned away from the suffering of my people.

344
00:38:18,178 --> 00:38:20,156
The infernal that destroyed us!

345
00:38:20,634 --> 00:38:22,572
<i>Die a death of flames!</i>

346
00:38:22,994 --> 00:38:25,505
Do not talk to me of dragonfire!

347
00:38:25,505 --> 00:38:28,233
I know it's wrath and ruin.

348
00:38:32,423 --> 00:38:38,430
I have faced... the great serpents of the north.

349
00:38:39,176 --> 00:38:43,417
I warned your grandfather, of what his greed would summon.

350
00:38:44,775 --> 00:38:48,370
But he would not listen.

351
00:38:51,112 --> 00:38:53,348
You are just like him.

352
00:38:55,897 --> 00:38:59,449
Stay here if you will and rot.

353
00:38:59,649 --> 00:39:03,562
A hundred years is a mere blink in a life of an elf.

354
00:39:03,934 --> 00:39:05,675
I am patient.

355
00:39:06,715 --> 00:39:09,232
I can wait.

356
00:39:16,092 --> 00:39:18,392
- Did he offer you a deal?  - He did.

357
00:39:20,206 --> 00:39:23,390
I told him he could go <i>and I'll shit upon your grave!</i>

358
00:39:24,350 --> 00:39:27,047
Him and all his kin!

359
00:39:27,523 --> 00:39:29,367
Well, that's that then.

360
00:39:30,068 --> 00:39:33,638
The deal... was our only hope.

361
00:39:36,589 --> 00:39:39,393
It's not our only hope.

362
00:39:45,416 --> 00:39:47,319
I know you are there.

363
00:39:48,693 --> 00:39:51,598
Why do you linger in the shadows?

364
00:39:52,907 --> 00:39:55,437
I was coming to report to you.

365
00:39:56,217 --> 00:39:59,784
I thought I ordered that nest to be destroyed not two moons past.

366
00:39:59,827 --> 00:40:02,383
We cleared the forest as ordered, my Lord.

367
00:40:02,383 --> 00:40:04,651
But more spiders keep coming up from the south.

368
00:40:04,651 --> 00:40:08,146
They're spawning in the ruins of Dol Guldur. If we could kill them at their source...

369
00:40:08,188 --> 00:40:10,632
That fortress lies beyond our borders.

370
00:40:10,646 --> 00:40:13,309
Keep our lands, clear of those foul creatures. That is your task.

371
00:40:13,503 --> 00:40:16,477
And when we drive them off, what then?

372
00:40:16,677 --> 00:40:18,494
Will they not spread to other lands?

373
00:40:18,494 --> 00:40:21,063
Other lands are not my concern.

374
00:40:21,996 --> 00:40:24,878
Fortunes of the world will rise and fall.

375
00:40:24,878 --> 00:40:28,498
But here in this kingdom, we will endure.

376
00:40:32,229 --> 00:40:34,749
Legolas said you fought well today.

377
00:40:39,083 --> 00:40:42,583
He's grown very fond of you.

378
00:40:43,698 --> 00:40:45,681
I assure you my Lord,

379
00:40:45,881 --> 00:40:48,907
Legolas thinks of me as no more than a captain of the guard.

380
00:40:49,303 --> 00:40:51,913
Perhaps he did... once.

381
00:40:51,990 --> 00:40:54,843
Now, I'm not so sure.

382
00:40:57,874 --> 00:41:00,666
I... do not think that you would allow your son

383
00:41:00,666 --> 00:41:03,342
to pledge himself to a lowly Silvan elf.

384
00:41:03,342 --> 00:41:06,987
No, you are right. l would not.

385
00:41:06,987 --> 00:41:09,675
Still, he cares about you.

386
00:41:09,711 --> 00:41:13,177
Do not give him hope, where there is none.

387
00:41:19,476 --> 00:41:21,527


388
00:41:21,972 --> 00:41:24,706


389
00:41:51,007 --> 00:41:54,779
The stone in your hand, What is it?

390
00:41:56,390 --> 00:41:58,069
It is a Talisman.

391
00:42:00,770 --> 00:42:02,774
A powerful spell has upon it.

392
00:42:02,774 --> 00:42:05,772
If any but a dwarf reads the runes on the stone,

393
00:42:06,488 --> 00:42:08,221
it will be forever cursed.

394
00:42:14,081 --> 00:42:16,380
Or not.

395
00:42:16,580 --> 00:42:19,417
Depending on whether you believe in that kind of thing. It's just a token.

396
00:42:22,422 --> 00:42:23,901
The Rune Stone.

397
00:42:23,999 --> 00:42:25,209


398
00:42:25,949 --> 00:42:28,684
My mother gave me it to me. So, I'd remember my promise.

399
00:42:30,528 --> 00:42:31,910
What promise?

400
00:42:32,110 --> 00:42:33,427
That I would come back to her.

401
00:42:36,650 --> 00:42:38,206
She worries.

402
00:42:39,292 --> 00:42:41,253
She thinks I'm reckless.

403
00:42:41,453 --> 00:42:42,453
Are you?

404
00:42:44,539 --> 00:42:46,170
Nah.

405
00:42:56,762 --> 00:42:59,758
Sounds like quite... a party, you're having up there.

406
00:43:00,711 --> 00:43:02,831
It is Mereth-en-Gilith.

407
00:43:03,031 --> 00:43:05,154
The Feast of Starlight.

408
00:43:06,272 --> 00:43:08,908
All light is sacred to the Eldar.

409
00:43:09,317 --> 00:43:12,521
But the Wood-elves loves best, the light of the stars.

410
00:43:13,373 --> 00:43:16,422
I always thought it is a cold light.

411
00:43:16,740 --> 00:43:19,110
Remote and far away.

412
00:43:20,751 --> 00:43:22,526
It is memory.

413
00:43:23,627 --> 00:43:25,862
Precious and pure.

414
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:31,268
Like your promise.

415
00:43:40,614 --> 00:43:43,305
I have walked there sometimes.

416
00:43:43,505 --> 00:43:46,684
Beyond the forest and up into the night.

417
00:43:47,971 --> 00:43:51,469
I have seen the world full away.

418
00:43:52,149 --> 00:43:55,387
And the white light, forever filled the air.

419
00:43:58,235 --> 00:44:01,233
I saw a fire moon once.

420
00:44:02,002 --> 00:44:06,387
It rose off the path near Dunland. Huge, red and golden it was, filled the sky.

421
00:44:08,634 --> 00:44:12,510
We were in escort with some merchants in Ered Luin. They were...

422
00:44:12,546 --> 00:44:16,095
trading in silver work for furs. We took the Greenway south,

423
00:44:16,295 --> 00:44:18,210
keeping the mountain to our left.

424
00:44:18,866 --> 00:44:20,398
But then, it appeared.

425
00:44:20,598 --> 00:44:24,613
This huge fire moon lights in our path.

426
00:44:24,613 --> 00:44:26,584
I wish I could show you...

427
00:44:28,588 --> 00:44:30,683
Galion, you old rogue! We're running out of drink.

428
00:44:31,901 --> 00:44:34,872
These empty barrels should have been sent to Esgaroth hours ago. 

429
00:44:34,872 --> 00:44:36,718
Bard have been waiting for them,

430
00:44:37,344 --> 00:44:41,923
Say what you like about our ill tempered King who has excellent taste in wine.

431
00:44:43,037 --> 00:44:44,890
Come, Elros, try it.

432
00:44:45,261 --> 00:44:47,054
I have the dwarves in my charge.

433
00:44:47,794 --> 00:44:50,163
They're locked up, where can they go?

434
00:44:53,759 --> 00:44:58,237
I'll wager the sun is on the rise. Must be nearly dawn.

435
00:44:58,237 --> 00:45:00,655
We never gonna reach the mountain, are we?

436
00:45:03,693 --> 00:45:05,594
Not stuck in here you're not.

437
00:45:11,966 --> 00:45:13,358
Bilbo!

438
00:45:16,110 --> 00:45:17,512
There are guards nearby!

439
00:45:38,026 --> 00:45:39,615
- What's that?  - You first.

440
00:45:39,719 --> 00:45:42,225
- Ori!  - Not that way. Down here... follow me!

441
00:45:42,225 --> 00:45:43,793
- Which way?  - Come on, go!

442
00:46:01,019 --> 00:46:02,164
This way.

443
00:46:04,998 --> 00:46:08,085
- Come on.  - I don't believe, we're in the cellars.

444
00:46:08,085 --> 00:46:10,073
You're supposed to be leading us unknown... further away.

445
00:46:10,073 --> 00:46:11,752
- I know what I'm doing.  - Shhh.

446
00:46:12,203 --> 00:46:13,648
Okay, this way. This way.

447
00:46:19,119 --> 00:46:21,743
Everyone, climb into the barrels... quickly!

448
00:46:21,743 --> 00:46:23,577
Are you mad? They will find us.

449
00:46:23,577 --> 00:46:25,137
No, no. They won't! I promise you.

450
00:46:25,137 --> 00:46:28,610
Please, please... You must trust me.

451
00:46:33,157 --> 00:46:34,494
Do as he says.

452
00:46:52,798 --> 00:46:54,711
What do we do now?

453
00:46:55,583 --> 00:46:58,126
- Hold your breath.  - Hold my breath... What do you mean?

454
00:47:23,908 --> 00:47:26,475
Where is the keeper of the keys?

455
00:47:31,850 --> 00:47:32,746
<i>Come now!</i>

456
00:47:52,911 --> 00:47:54,458
Well done, Master Baggins.

457
00:47:55,807 --> 00:47:58,280
Go, come on let's go!

458
00:48:06,823 --> 00:48:09,472
Hold on!

459
00:48:21,878 --> 00:48:23,248
Bilbo!

460
00:48:37,011 --> 00:48:38,388


461
00:48:57,868 --> 00:48:59,189
No!

462
00:49:12,027 --> 00:49:12,978
Watch out!

463
00:49:27,128 --> 00:49:29,584
<i>Kill them! Quickly!</i>

464
00:49:30,101 --> 00:49:32,520


465
00:49:33,711 --> 00:49:34,648
Get over the bridge!

466
00:49:47,688 --> 00:49:48,916
Die!

467
00:50:13,201 --> 00:50:14,579
Kili!

468
00:50:21,222 --> 00:50:22,045
Kili!

469
00:50:36,222 --> 00:50:39,245


470
00:51:04,970 --> 00:51:06,661
<i>The dwarves are escaping!</i>

471
00:51:07,067 --> 00:51:08,583


472
00:51:15,853 --> 00:51:16,779
Kili!

473
00:52:40,617 --> 00:52:41,943
Nori!

474
00:52:54,547 --> 00:52:55,832
Cut the log!

475
00:53:03,723 --> 00:53:04,800
Bombur!

476
00:54:40,317 --> 00:54:41,386
<i>Tauriel!</i>

477
00:54:41,386 --> 00:54:42,863


478
00:54:43,951 --> 00:54:47,639


479
00:54:48,667 --> 00:54:52,574


480
00:54:57,048 --> 00:54:59,492
<i>Don't let them go away!</i>

481
00:56:39,074 --> 00:56:40,769
Oh, it's you.

482
00:56:40,769 --> 00:56:41,969
Why am I here, Gandalf?

483
00:56:42,209 --> 00:56:46,245
Trust me, Radagast. I would not have call you here without good reason.

484
00:56:51,078 --> 00:56:54,570
- This is not a nice place to meet.  - No.

485
00:56:55,751 --> 00:56:58,247
It is not.

486
00:56:58,326 --> 00:57:01,425
These are dark spells, Gandalf.

487
00:57:01,425 --> 00:57:04,583
Old... And full of hate.

488
00:57:04,583 --> 00:57:05,783
Who's buried here?

489
00:57:05,983 --> 00:57:09,518
If he had a name, it's long since been lost.

490
00:57:09,718 --> 00:57:13,808
He would've been known only as a servant of evil.

491
00:57:16,850 --> 00:57:19,221
One of a number.

492
00:57:22,836 --> 00:57:25,502
One of nine.

493
00:57:27,749 --> 00:57:29,518
Why now, Gandalf?

494
00:57:29,518 --> 00:57:33,102
- I don't understand!  - The Ringwraiths have been summoned to Dol Guldur.

495
00:57:33,102 --> 00:57:35,525
But, it cannot be the Necromancer.

496
00:57:35,725 --> 00:57:38,791
A human sorcerer could not summon such evil.

497
00:57:39,251 --> 00:57:41,479
Who said it was human.

498
00:57:42,750 --> 00:57:46,234
And, Nine only answers to One Master.

499
00:57:46,274 --> 00:57:49,484
We've been blind, Radagast.

500
00:57:49,484 --> 00:57:50,879
And in our blindness...

501
00:57:51,725 --> 00:57:54,461
The Enemy has returned.

502
00:57:56,218 --> 00:57:58,667
He is summoning his servants.

503
00:57:59,140 --> 00:58:03,561
Azog the Defiler is no ordinary hunter.

504
00:58:03,561 --> 00:58:07,614
He is a commander, the commander of legions.

505
00:58:07,814 --> 00:58:11,543
The Enemy... is preparing for war.

506
00:58:12,698 --> 00:58:16,997
Which will begin in the east. His mind is set upon that mountain.

507
00:58:17,651 --> 00:58:19,101
- Where are you going?  - To rejoin the others.

508
00:58:19,377 --> 00:58:21,006
Gandalf?!

509
00:58:21,206 --> 00:58:24,876
I started this. I cannot forsake them.

510
00:58:24,876 --> 00:58:26,587
They're in grave danger.

511
00:58:26,587 --> 00:58:27,965
If what you say is true.

512
00:58:28,607 --> 00:58:32,000
The world is in grave danger.

513
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:36,686
The power in that fortress will only grow stronger.

514
00:58:36,731 --> 00:58:40,700
You want me to cast my friends aside.

515
00:58:43,595 --> 00:58:44,751
Anything behind us?

516
00:58:44,951 --> 00:58:46,219
Not that I can see.

517
00:58:50,609 --> 00:58:54,016
- I think we've outrun the Orcs.  - Not for long. We've lost the current.

518
00:58:54,486 --> 00:58:55,754
We are almost half drowned!

519
00:58:56,727 --> 00:58:58,201
Make for the shore!

520
00:58:58,866 --> 00:59:00,366
Come on! Let's go.

521
00:59:20,191 --> 00:59:21,678
I'm fine, it's nothing.

522
00:59:22,067 --> 00:59:25,887
- On your feet.  - Kili is wounded. His leg needs binding.

523
00:59:25,887 --> 00:59:28,647
There's an Orc pack at our tail. We keep moving.

524
00:59:28,647 --> 00:59:31,643
- To where?  - To the mountain. We are so close.

525
00:59:31,843 --> 00:59:34,868
A lake lies between us and that mountain.

526
00:59:34,912 --> 00:59:37,575
- We have no way to cross it.  - So then, we go arround.

527
00:59:37,575 --> 00:59:40,423
The Orcs will run us down, as sure as daylight.

528
00:59:40,798 --> 00:59:43,282
We have no weapons to defend ourselves.

529
00:59:43,282 --> 00:59:44,482
Bind his leg, quickly.

530
00:59:45,522 --> 00:59:48,035
We have two minutes.

531
01:00:07,206 --> 01:00:10,516
Do it again and you are dead.

532
01:00:12,397 --> 01:00:15,912
Excuse me, but uh... You're from Lake-town?

533
01:00:15,912 --> 01:00:17,112
If I'm not mistaken.

534
01:00:18,248 --> 01:00:20,747
That barge over there,

535
01:00:20,747 --> 01:00:24,481
it wouldn't be available for hire by any chance?

536
01:00:25,838 --> 01:00:28,252
What makes you think, I would help you?

537
01:00:28,452 --> 01:00:30,355
Those boots have seen better days.

538
01:00:30,555 --> 01:00:32,348
As has that coat.

539
01:00:32,548 --> 01:00:35,493
I've no doubts you have some hungry mouths to feed.

540
01:00:36,683 --> 01:00:38,208
How many bairns?

541
01:00:38,408 --> 01:00:40,545
A boy and two girls.

542
01:00:40,918 --> 01:00:44,588
And your wife, I imagine she's as a beauty?

543
01:00:45,031 --> 01:00:46,433
Aye.

544
01:00:46,770 --> 01:00:48,239
She was.

545
01:00:51,016 --> 01:00:55,801
- I'm sorry, I didn't mean to...  - Oh, come on! C'mon, enough with the niceties.

546
01:00:56,286 --> 01:00:59,310
- What's your hurry?  - What's it to you?

547
01:00:59,510 --> 01:01:00,510
I would like to know who you are.

548
01:01:01,360 --> 01:01:04,091
And what you are doing in these lands.

549
01:01:04,291 --> 01:01:07,046
We are simple merchants, from the Blue Mountains.

550
01:01:07,046 --> 01:01:10,417
Journeying to see our kin in the Iron Hills.

551
01:01:11,177 --> 01:01:13,580
Simple merchants, you say?

552
01:01:13,780 --> 01:01:17,557
We need food, supplies, weapons.

553
01:01:17,557 --> 01:01:19,194
Can you help us?

554
01:01:23,014 --> 01:01:25,805
I know where these barrels came from.

555
01:01:26,005 --> 01:01:30,128
- What of it?  - I don't know what business you had with the elves.

556
01:01:30,328 --> 01:01:32,951
But, I don't think it ended well.

557
01:01:34,001 --> 01:01:37,261
No one enters Lake-town but by lead of the master.

558
01:01:37,261 --> 01:01:40,647
All his wealth comes from trade with the Woodland realm.

559
01:01:40,647 --> 01:01:43,878
He would see you in irons before risking the wrath of King Thranduil.

560
01:01:45,406 --> 01:01:46,699
Offer him more.

561
01:01:49,304 --> 01:01:52,251
I'll wager there are ways to enter that town unseen.

562
01:01:52,451 --> 01:01:53,934
Aye.

563
01:01:54,981 --> 01:01:56,964
But for that...

564
01:01:57,881 --> 01:02:00,319
- you would need a smuggler.  - For which we would pay.

565
01:02:00,319 --> 01:02:01,414
Double.

566
01:02:09,926 --> 01:02:12,955
Such is the nature of evil.

567
01:02:13,155 --> 01:02:18,244
Out there in the vast, ignorance of the world it festers and spreads.

568
01:02:18,244 --> 01:02:21,098
A shadow that grows in the dark.

569
01:02:21,098 --> 01:02:26,668
A sleepless malice as black as the oncoming wall of night.

570
01:02:27,631 --> 01:02:32,334
So it ever was... So will it always be.

571
01:02:33,269 --> 01:02:37,043
In time, all foul things come forth.

572
01:02:37,376 --> 01:02:41,598
You were tracking a company of thirteen dwarves, why?

573
01:02:41,598 --> 01:02:45,054
Not thirteen, not anymore.

574
01:02:45,553 --> 01:02:49,244
The young one, the black head archer.

575
01:02:49,444 --> 01:02:52,473
We stuck him with a Morgul shaft.

576
01:02:53,229 --> 01:02:55,462
The poison's in his blood.

577
01:02:55,662 --> 01:02:57,480
He'll be choking on it soon.

578
01:02:58,395 --> 01:03:00,022
Answer the question, filth!

579
01:03:00,399 --> 01:03:03,107


580
01:03:05,552 --> 01:03:07,930
I would not antagonize her.

581
01:03:07,930 --> 01:03:09,602
You like killing things, Orc?

582
01:03:11,028 --> 01:03:12,736
You like death?

583
01:03:13,978 --> 01:03:14,883
Then, let me give it to you!

584
01:03:14,983 --> 01:03:16,058


585
01:03:16,526 --> 01:03:18,342


586
01:03:18,880 --> 01:03:20,161


587
01:03:30,922 --> 01:03:35,347
I do not care about one dead Dwarf. Answer the question.

588
01:03:35,547 --> 01:03:37,552
You have nothing to fear.

589
01:03:38,453 --> 01:03:41,538
Tell us what you know and I will set you free.

590
01:03:42,095 --> 01:03:44,550
You had orders to kill them, why?

591
01:03:44,550 --> 01:03:46,861
What is Thorin Oakenshield to you?

592
01:03:46,861 --> 01:03:51,170
- The dwarf runt will never be king.  - King?!

593
01:03:51,170 --> 01:03:54,128
There is no king under the mountain, nor will there ever be.

594
01:03:54,775 --> 01:03:57,126
None would dare enter Erebor.

595
01:03:57,126 --> 01:04:00,463
- Whilst the dragon lives.  - You know nothing.

596
01:04:00,663 --> 01:04:03,348
Your world will burn.

597
01:04:03,348 --> 01:04:06,531
What are you talking about? Speak!

598
01:04:07,342 --> 01:04:09,959
Our time has come again.

599
01:04:10,511 --> 01:04:15,161
My master serves... The One.

600
01:04:15,361 --> 01:04:18,030
Do you understand now, Elfling?

601
01:04:18,030 --> 01:04:19,900
Death is upon you.

602
01:04:19,900 --> 01:04:24,154
The flames... of war, are upon you!

603
01:04:27,214 --> 01:04:28,795
Why did you do that?

604
01:04:28,795 --> 01:04:30,792
You promised to set him free.

605
01:04:30,792 --> 01:04:32,365
And I did.

606
01:04:32,883 --> 01:04:37,743
I freed his wretched head from his miserable shoulders.

607
01:04:38,206 --> 01:04:40,537
There was more the orc could tell us.

608
01:04:40,737 --> 01:04:43,358
There was nothing more he could tell me.

609
01:04:44,023 --> 01:04:46,755
What did he mean by the flames of war?

610
01:04:46,955 --> 01:04:52,076
It means they intend to unleash a weapon so great, it will destroy all before it.

611
01:04:52,762 --> 01:04:56,186
I want the watch doubled at our borders, all roads, all rivers.

612
01:04:56,186 --> 01:04:58,258
Nothing moves but I hear of it.

613
01:04:58,258 --> 01:04:59,891
No one enters this kingdom...

614
01:05:01,067 --> 01:05:03,199
And no one leaves it.

615
01:05:05,821 --> 01:05:07,234


616
01:05:07,720 --> 01:05:10,719


617
01:05:11,596 --> 01:05:12,768


618
01:05:15,601 --> 01:05:16,762


619
01:05:17,141 --> 01:05:18,371


620
01:05:19,345 --> 01:05:20,984


621
01:05:21,591 --> 01:05:23,178


622
01:05:46,838 --> 01:05:48,780


623
01:05:49,123 --> 01:05:50,203


624
01:05:50,822 --> 01:05:53,488


625
01:05:57,471 --> 01:05:59,108


626
01:06:03,319 --> 01:06:06,296


627
01:06:27,893 --> 01:06:29,053
Watch out!

628
01:06:37,922 --> 01:06:40,361
What are you trying to do, drown us?

629
01:06:40,361 --> 01:06:43,427
I was born and bred on these waters, Master Dwarf.

630
01:06:43,427 --> 01:06:46,794
If I wanted to drown you, I would not do it here.

631
01:06:48,771 --> 01:06:51,389
Oh, I've had enough of this lippy lake-man.

632
01:06:51,389 --> 01:06:52,904
I say, we throw him off the side...

633
01:06:52,904 --> 01:06:56,227
- and be done with him.  - No, Bard... His name is Bard.

634
01:06:56,227 --> 01:06:57,333
How do you know?

635
01:06:57,333 --> 01:07:01,839
- Ah, I asked him.  - I don't care what he calls himself, I don't like him.

636
01:07:01,839 --> 01:07:05,463
We do not have to like him. We simply have to pay him.

637
01:07:05,663 --> 01:07:08,593
Come on now, lads. Turn out your pockets.

638
01:07:09,577 --> 01:07:12,748
- How do we know he won't betray us?  - We don't.

639
01:07:14,019 --> 01:07:17,094
There's um... just a wee problem.

640
01:07:17,094 --> 01:07:19,267
We are ten coins short.

641
01:07:20,695 --> 01:07:22,021
Gloin.

642
01:07:23,132 --> 01:07:24,880
Come on, give us what you have.

643
01:07:24,924 --> 01:07:27,024
Don't look to me.

644
01:07:27,024 --> 01:07:30,996
I have been bled dry by this venture.

645
01:07:30,996 --> 01:07:34,163
What have I seen for my investment?

646
01:07:34,363 --> 01:07:38,008
Nought but misery, grief, and...

647
01:07:45,713 --> 01:07:47,881
Bless, my beard.

648
01:07:48,293 --> 01:07:49,830
Take it.

649
01:07:49,830 --> 01:07:52,192
Take all of it.

650
01:07:56,111 --> 01:07:57,565
The money, quick! Give it to me.

651
01:07:57,565 --> 01:08:00,169
We will pay you when we get our provisions. But not before.

652
01:08:00,169 --> 01:08:02,924
If you value your freedom, you will do as I say.

653
01:08:02,924 --> 01:08:05,490
There are guards ahead.

654
01:08:22,787 --> 01:08:24,288
Ssh. What is he doing?

655
01:08:24,925 --> 01:08:26,617
He is talking to someone.

656
01:08:28,568 --> 01:08:30,465
He is... pointing right at us.

657
01:08:33,473 --> 01:08:35,724
- Now they're shaking hands.  - What?

658
01:08:36,284 --> 01:08:38,160
He's selling us out.

659
01:08:58,798 --> 01:09:00,685
Oh, good God!

660
01:09:00,885 --> 01:09:01,885
Quite!

661
01:09:04,483 --> 01:09:06,129
We are approaching the toll gate.

662
01:09:17,504 --> 01:09:20,075
Halt! Goods inspection.

663
01:09:20,778 --> 01:09:22,570
Papers, please!

664
01:09:23,404 --> 01:09:26,038
- Oh, it's you, Bard!  - Morning, Percy.

665
01:09:26,038 --> 01:09:28,731
- Anything to declare?  - Nothing,

666
01:09:28,731 --> 01:09:31,945
but I am cold and tired. I'm ready for home.

667
01:09:31,945 --> 01:09:34,490
You and me, both.

668
01:09:37,246 --> 01:09:40,097
There we are, all in order.

669
01:09:40,097 --> 01:09:43,151
Not... so... fast.

670
01:09:43,598 --> 01:09:46,193
Consignment of empty barrels,

671
01:09:46,393 --> 01:09:48,319
from the Woodland realm.

672
01:09:48,893 --> 01:09:51,322
Only...

673
01:09:51,619 --> 01:09:55,528
they are not empty, are they, Bard?

674
01:09:55,528 --> 01:10:00,024
If I recall correctly, you're licensed as a bargeman.

675
01:10:00,252 --> 01:10:02,522
Not...

676
01:10:02,522 --> 01:10:04,102
a fisherman.

677
01:10:04,103 --> 01:10:05,886
That's none of your business.

678
01:10:06,086 --> 01:10:10,943
Wrong. It's the Master's business, which makes it my business.

679
01:10:10,943 --> 01:10:13,887
Oh, come on... Alfrid. Have a heart. People need to eat!

680
01:10:13,887 --> 01:10:16,907
These fish are illegal.

681
01:10:17,151 --> 01:10:18,735
Empty barrels over the side.

682
01:10:18,735 --> 01:10:20,720
- You heard him.  - In the canal.

683
01:10:21,935 --> 01:10:23,820
Come on... Get a move on.

684
01:10:24,241 --> 01:10:26,516
Folk in this town are struggling.

685
01:10:26,516 --> 01:10:28,951
Times are hard. Food is scarce.

686
01:10:28,994 --> 01:10:30,754
That's not my problem.

687
01:10:30,754 --> 01:10:34,461
And when people hear the Master is dumping fish back in the lake?

688
01:10:34,661 --> 01:10:36,733
When the rioting starts?

689
01:10:39,371 --> 01:10:42,137
Will it be your problem, then?

690
01:10:45,721 --> 01:10:47,522
Stop!

691
01:10:50,102 --> 01:10:53,079
Ever the people's champion, eh, Bard?

692
01:10:53,079 --> 01:10:56,634
Protector of the common folk. You might have their favor now, bargeman,

693
01:10:56,634 --> 01:10:58,329
but it won't last.

694
01:11:01,920 --> 01:11:03,437
Raise the gate!

695
01:11:06,259 --> 01:11:09,956
The Master has his eyes on you. You'll do well to remember.

696
01:11:09,956 --> 01:11:11,707
We know where you live.

697
01:11:11,707 --> 01:11:12,907
It's a small town, Alfrid.

698
01:11:14,161 --> 01:11:17,158
Everyone knows where everyone lives.

699
01:11:32,580 --> 01:11:34,808
All this talk of civil unrest,

700
01:11:34,808 --> 01:11:36,980
someone's been stirring the pot, Sire.

701
01:11:40,202 --> 01:11:41,520
Gout playing out, Sire?

702
01:11:41,554 --> 01:11:43,527
It's the damp! It's the only possible explanation.

703
01:11:43,727 --> 01:11:45,480
Now, get me a brandy.

704
01:11:46,639 --> 01:11:49,566
The mood of the people, Sire. It's turning ugly.

705
01:11:49,566 --> 01:11:50,766
They are commoners, Alfrid.

706
01:11:50,889 --> 01:11:52,887
They've always been ugly.

707
01:11:52,887 --> 01:11:57,215
It's not my fault they live in a place that stinks of fish, oil and tar.

708
01:11:57,644 --> 01:12:02,995
Jobs, shelter... food. It's all they ever bleat about.

709
01:12:02,995 --> 01:12:06,938
It's my believe, Sire, they're being lead on by troublemakers.

710
01:12:07,548 --> 01:12:11,894
Then, we must find these troublemakers. And arrest them.

711
01:12:11,894 --> 01:12:13,643
My thoughts exactly, Sire.

712
01:12:13,637 --> 01:12:17,216
And all this talk of a change must be suppressed.

713
01:12:17,216 --> 01:12:21,037
We can't afford to let the rabble band together, start making noises.

714
01:12:21,037 --> 01:12:24,662
The next thing you know, they will start asking questions,

715
01:12:24,662 --> 01:12:26,049
forming committees.

716
01:12:27,247 --> 01:12:28,950
Launching enquiries.

717
01:12:28,950 --> 01:12:31,843
Out with the old, in with the new.

718
01:12:32,043 --> 01:12:33,043
What?

719
01:12:33,441 --> 01:12:35,297
That's what I've been saying, Sire.

720
01:12:35,297 --> 01:12:38,956
- There is even talk... of an election.  - An election?

721
01:12:39,430 --> 01:12:42,566
That's absurd! I won't stand for it.

722
01:12:43,816 --> 01:12:45,884
I don't think they'd ask you to stand, Sire.

723
01:12:48,759 --> 01:12:51,071
Shirkers, ingrates!

724
01:12:51,071 --> 01:12:52,170
Rabble rousers!

725
01:12:52,170 --> 01:12:55,715
Who would have the nerve to question my authority?

726
01:12:55,915 --> 01:12:58,903
Who would dare! Who?

727
01:13:03,062 --> 01:13:05,049
Bard!

728
01:13:05,049 --> 01:13:10,334
You mark my words, that... trouble making bargeman is behind all this.

729
01:13:17,768 --> 01:13:19,779
Get your hands off me!

730
01:13:26,465 --> 01:13:28,736
You didn't see them. They were never here.

731
01:13:29,710 --> 01:13:31,741
The fish, you can have for nothing.

732
01:13:34,445 --> 01:13:35,549
Follow me!

733
01:13:44,896 --> 01:13:46,054
Da!

734
01:13:46,578 --> 01:13:49,091
Our house... It's being watched!

735
01:14:24,742 --> 01:14:26,841
You can tell the Master I am done for the day.

736
01:14:27,953 --> 01:14:29,549
Da!

737
01:14:29,592 --> 01:14:30,885
Where have you been?

738
01:14:31,085 --> 01:14:34,120
Father, there you are! I was worried.

739
01:14:34,120 --> 01:14:35,358
Here, Sigrid.

740
01:14:36,146 --> 01:14:37,653
Bain, get them in.

741
01:14:45,115 --> 01:14:49,529
If you speak of this to anyone, I'll rip your hands off!

742
01:14:52,137 --> 01:14:53,672
Get it off.

743
01:14:55,075 --> 01:14:56,589
Up there.

744
01:15:04,786 --> 01:15:07,383
Da, why the dwarves climbing out of our toilet?

745
01:15:07,383 --> 01:15:09,461
Will they bring us luck?

746
01:15:12,927 --> 01:15:15,886
They may not be the best fit, but they will keep you warm.

747
01:15:16,086 --> 01:15:18,534
Oh, it's fine. Thank you.

748
01:15:28,308 --> 01:15:30,971
The dwarvish wind-lance!

749
01:15:30,971 --> 01:15:32,171
You look like you've seen a ghost.

750
01:15:33,355 --> 01:15:35,523
He has.

751
01:15:35,564 --> 01:15:38,456
The last time we saw such a weapon,

752
01:15:38,656 --> 01:15:41,729
the city was on fire.

753
01:15:42,288 --> 01:15:44,351
It was the day the dragon came.

754
01:15:47,674 --> 01:15:50,391
The day that Smaug destroyed Dale.

755
01:15:52,891 --> 01:15:57,843
Girion, the lord of the city, rallied his bowmen to fire upon the beast.

756
01:15:58,346 --> 01:16:02,850
But, a dragon's hide is tough. Tougher than the strongest armor.

757
01:16:03,529 --> 01:16:06,864
Only a black arrow fired from a wind-lance

758
01:16:06,864 --> 01:16:09,572
could have pierced the dragon's hide.

759
01:16:09,572 --> 01:16:12,913
And few of those arrows were ever made.

760
01:16:17,952 --> 01:16:22,742
The store was running low when Girion made his last attempt.

761
01:16:29,189 --> 01:16:32,224
The aim of men had been true that day,

762
01:16:33,136 --> 01:16:35,335
much would be different.

763
01:16:38,957 --> 01:16:41,221
You speak as if you were there.

764
01:16:42,437 --> 01:16:44,772
All dwarves know the tale.

765
01:16:44,772 --> 01:16:47,278
And, you would know that Girion hit the dragon.

766
01:16:47,478 --> 01:16:49,441
He loosened a scale under the left wing.

767
01:16:49,441 --> 01:16:51,629
One more shot and he would have killed the beast.

768
01:16:52,575 --> 01:16:56,015
That's a fairy story, lad. Nothing more.

769
01:16:57,054 --> 01:16:59,462
You took our money.

770
01:16:59,498 --> 01:17:01,996
Where are the weapons?

771
01:17:03,312 --> 01:17:04,897
Wait here.

772
01:17:19,471 --> 01:17:21,305
Tomorrow begins the last days of Autumn.

773
01:17:21,305 --> 01:17:23,777
Durin's day falls the morning after next.

774
01:17:23,977 --> 01:17:26,165
We must reach the mountain before then.

775
01:17:26,165 --> 01:17:27,502
And, if we do not?

776
01:17:27,702 --> 01:17:30,703
If we fail to find the hidden door before that time,

777
01:17:30,703 --> 01:17:32,535
then this quest has been for nothing.

778
01:17:44,056 --> 01:17:47,063
- What is this?  - Pike hook.

779
01:17:47,722 --> 01:17:49,170
Made from an old harpoon.

780
01:17:49,344 --> 01:17:51,146
- And this?  - A crowbill, we call it.

781
01:17:51,185 --> 01:17:53,058
Fashioned from a smithy's hammer.

782
01:17:53,258 --> 01:17:54,969
It's heavy in hand, I grand. But...

783
01:17:54,969 --> 01:17:58,240
In defense of your life, these will serve you better than none.

784
01:17:58,240 --> 01:18:01,070
We paid you for weapons.

785
01:18:01,270 --> 01:18:04,255
Iron forged, swords and axes!

786
01:18:04,455 --> 01:18:06,134
It's a joke!

787
01:18:07,360 --> 01:18:10,134
You won't find better outside the city armory.

788
01:18:10,134 --> 01:18:12,965
All iron forged weapons are held there under lock and key.

789
01:18:12,965 --> 01:18:16,784
Thorin, why not take what's on offer and go?

790
01:18:16,784 --> 01:18:19,143
I've made do with less, so have you.

791
01:18:21,385 --> 01:18:24,109
- I say, we leave now.  - You're not going anywhere!

792
01:18:24,109 --> 01:18:26,554
- What did you say?  - There are spies watching this house,

793
01:18:26,554 --> 01:18:29,081
and probably every dock and wharf in the town.

794
01:18:30,057 --> 01:18:31,822
You must wait till nightfall.

795
01:18:48,035 --> 01:18:49,789
Thorin.

796
01:19:02,449 --> 01:19:04,129
Da?

797
01:19:06,519 --> 01:19:08,418
Don't let them leave.

798
01:19:33,394 --> 01:19:35,128


799
01:19:35,596 --> 01:19:36,991


800
01:19:37,500 --> 01:19:38,654


801
01:19:40,242 --> 01:19:41,844
Tauriel...

802
01:19:42,044 --> 01:19:45,521
You cannot hunt thirty orcs on your own.

803
01:19:45,521 --> 01:19:47,559
But I'm not on my own.

804
01:19:48,320 --> 01:19:50,297
You knew I would come.

805
01:19:52,019 --> 01:19:53,996
The King is angry, Tauriel.

806
01:19:54,444 --> 01:19:57,700
For 600 years my father has protected you, favoured you...

807
01:19:57,738 --> 01:20:01,079
you defied his orders. You betrayed his trust.

808
01:20:02,958 --> 01:20:04,293


809
01:20:04,293 --> 01:20:06,272


810
01:20:06,292 --> 01:20:07,585


811
01:20:07,894 --> 01:20:10,673


812
01:20:11,053 --> 01:20:14,165
The King has never let orc filth roam our lands.

813
01:20:14,165 --> 01:20:17,551
But he would let these orc packs cross our borders and kill our prisoners.

814
01:20:17,751 --> 01:20:19,151
It is not our fight.

815
01:20:19,151 --> 01:20:20,291
It is our fight.

816
01:20:21,057 --> 01:20:23,106
It will not end here.

817
01:20:23,106 --> 01:20:26,083
With every victory, this evil will grow.

818
01:20:26,409 --> 01:20:29,313
If your father has his way, we will do nothing.

819
01:20:29,313 --> 01:20:31,469
We will hide withing our walls.

820
01:20:31,469 --> 01:20:34,384
Live our lives away from the light...

821
01:20:34,384 --> 01:20:36,577
and let darkness descend.

822
01:20:37,315 --> 01:20:39,975
Are we not part of this world?

823
01:20:40,850 --> 01:20:42,295
Tell me, <i>mellon</i>,

824
01:20:42,295 --> 01:20:45,368
When did we let evil become stronger than us?

825
01:20:50,394 --> 01:20:52,836
Hello Bard, who are you after?

826
01:20:54,457 --> 01:20:55,997
There was a tapestry.

827
01:20:56,217 --> 01:20:57,447
An old one.

828
01:20:57,721 --> 01:21:00,160
- Where is it gone?  - What tapestry are you talking about?

829
01:21:00,766 --> 01:21:01,687
This one!

830
01:21:01,887 --> 01:21:05,215
They were dwarves I tell you. Appeared out of nowhere.

831
01:21:05,215 --> 01:21:08,787
Full beards, fierce eyes. I've never seen the like.

832
01:21:09,397 --> 01:21:13,034
- What are dwarves doing in these parts?  - It's the prophecy.

833
01:21:13,034 --> 01:21:16,583
- What prophecy?  - Prophecy of Durin's folk.

834
01:21:24,316 --> 01:21:26,553
Prophecy?

835
01:21:29,807 --> 01:21:30,875
Prophecy.

836
01:21:30,875 --> 01:21:32,900
The old tales may come true.

837
01:21:32,900 --> 01:21:35,096
Vast golds and treasure!

838
01:21:35,096 --> 01:21:38,859
Can it really be true? Has the Lord of Silver Fountains returned?

839
01:21:39,773 --> 01:21:42,713
The Lord of Silver Fountains.

840
01:21:42,713 --> 01:21:44,968
The King of Carven Stone.

841
01:21:46,797 --> 01:21:49,615
The king beneath the mountain...

842
01:21:49,615 --> 01:21:51,959
shall come into his own.

843
01:21:53,164 --> 01:21:57,507
And the bells shall ring in gladness at the Mountain King's return.

844
01:21:58,014 --> 01:22:00,787
But all shall fade in sadness.

845
01:22:01,215 --> 01:22:05,061
And the lake will shine and burn.

846
01:22:06,396 --> 01:22:09,639
- Da, I tried to stop them.  - How long have they been gone?!

847
01:22:14,138 --> 01:22:15,653
Shh. Keep it down.

848
01:22:15,653 --> 01:22:18,350
As soon as we have the weapons, we'll make straight for the mountain.

849
01:22:18,550 --> 01:22:19,550
Go... go... go!

850
01:22:24,559 --> 01:22:25,690
Next!

851
01:22:38,933 --> 01:22:42,524
- Are you alright?  - I can manage.

852
01:22:42,524 --> 01:22:43,724
Let's just get out of here.

853
01:22:58,098 --> 01:22:59,210
Run!

854
01:23:28,678 --> 01:23:30,503
What is the meaning of this?

855
01:23:30,703 --> 01:23:32,687
We caught them stealing weapons, Sire.

856
01:23:32,687 --> 01:23:35,826
Ah, enemies of the state... eh?

857
01:23:35,826 --> 01:23:39,088
A desperate bunch of mercenaries, if ever there was, Sire.

858
01:23:39,088 --> 01:23:40,777
Hold your tongue!

859
01:23:42,945 --> 01:23:45,745
You do not know to whom you speak!

860
01:23:45,745 --> 01:23:47,750
This is no common criminal.

861
01:23:47,750 --> 01:23:51,243
This is Thorin. Son of Thrain...

862
01:23:51,243 --> 01:23:52,443
Son of Thror.

863
01:23:55,705 --> 01:23:58,182
We are the dwarves of Erebor.

864
01:24:00,179 --> 01:24:03,163
We have come to reclaim our homeland.

865
01:24:08,517 --> 01:24:11,630
I remember this town in the great days of old.

866
01:24:12,666 --> 01:24:17,326
Fleets of boats lay at harbor, filled with silks and fine gems.

867
01:24:17,326 --> 01:24:20,201
This was no forsaken town on a lake...

868
01:24:20,401 --> 01:24:24,810
This was the center of all trade in the north.

869
01:24:25,831 --> 01:24:27,905
I will see those days returned.

870
01:24:27,905 --> 01:24:30,438
I would relight the great forges of the dwarves

871
01:24:30,849 --> 01:24:34,884
and send wealth and riches flowing once more from the halls of Erebor!

872
01:24:37,562 --> 01:24:38,903
Death!

873
01:24:38,903 --> 01:24:41,583
That is what you will bring upon us.

874
01:24:42,027 --> 01:24:44,983
Dragon fire and ruin.

875
01:24:46,244 --> 01:24:48,718
If you awaken that beast,

876
01:24:49,230 --> 01:24:50,783
it will destroy us all.

877
01:24:50,982 --> 01:24:54,631
You can listen to this naysayer, but I promise you this:

878
01:24:57,150 --> 01:24:58,579
If we succeed,

879
01:24:59,895 --> 01:25:03,194
all will share in the wealth of the mountain.

880
01:25:06,970 --> 01:25:11,408
You will have enough gold to rebuild Esgaroth ten times over!

881
01:25:13,269 --> 01:25:16,039
All of you, listen to me!

882
01:25:16,039 --> 01:25:19,574
You must listen. Have you forgotten what happened to Dale?

883
01:25:21,221 --> 01:25:23,879
Have you forgotten those who died in the firestorm?

884
01:25:24,037 --> 01:25:25,037
No!

885
01:25:26,438 --> 01:25:28,124
And for what purpose?

886
01:25:28,957 --> 01:25:31,680
The blind ambition of a Mountain King,

887
01:25:31,680 --> 01:25:35,581
so driven by greed, he could not see beyond his own desire!

888
01:25:37,259 --> 01:25:43,646
Now, now! We must not, any of us, be too quick to lay blame.

889
01:25:44,599 --> 01:25:49,157
Let us not forget, that it was Girion, lord of Dale,

890
01:25:49,157 --> 01:25:53,609
your ancestor, who failed to kill the beast!

891
01:25:56,297 --> 01:25:59,536
He is true, Sire. We all know the story.

892
01:26:00,282 --> 01:26:05,924
Arrow after arrow, he shot. Each one missing it's mark.

893
01:26:12,326 --> 01:26:13,882
You have no right.

894
01:26:15,223 --> 01:26:17,266
No right to enter that mountain.

895
01:26:19,006 --> 01:26:21,667
I have the only right.

896
01:26:27,293 --> 01:26:30,626
I speak to the Master of the men of the lake.

897
01:26:30,626 --> 01:26:32,619
Will you see the prophecy fulfilled?

898
01:26:34,136 --> 01:26:39,736
Will you share in the great wealth of our people?

899
01:26:44,089 --> 01:26:46,071
What say you?

900
01:26:49,253 --> 01:26:52,755
I say unto you...

901
01:26:53,658 --> 01:26:55,628
welcome!

902
01:26:55,628 --> 01:27:01,063
Welcome and rise! Welcome, King Under the Mountain!

903
01:27:12,815 --> 01:27:14,225
You do know we're one short?

904
01:27:14,225 --> 01:27:16,775
- Where is Bofur?  - He is not here, we'll leave him behind.

905
01:27:16,775 --> 01:27:17,975
We will have to,

906
01:27:18,021 --> 01:27:21,431
if we are to find the door before nightfall. We can risk no more delays.

907
01:27:26,305 --> 01:27:27,458
Not you.

908
01:27:27,658 --> 01:27:30,424
We must travel at speed. You will slow us down.

909
01:27:31,330 --> 01:27:33,273
What are you talking about? I'm coming with you.

910
01:27:33,273 --> 01:27:34,273
No, no.

911
01:27:39,761 --> 01:27:42,047
I'm going to be there when that door's opened.

912
01:27:42,047 --> 01:27:44,405
When we first look upon the halls of our fathers, Thorin...

913
01:27:44,405 --> 01:27:48,965
Kili, stay here... rest.

914
01:27:48,965 --> 01:27:51,168
Join us when you're healed.

915
01:27:56,523 --> 01:27:59,750
I'll stay with the lad. My duty lies with the wounded.

916
01:27:59,750 --> 01:28:00,950
Uncle...

917
01:28:01,697 --> 01:28:04,912
we grew up on tales of the mountain. Tales you told us...

918
01:28:04,957 --> 01:28:06,779
You cannot take that away from him.

919
01:28:06,779 --> 01:28:08,602
- Fili.  - I will carry him, if I must.

920
01:28:08,602 --> 01:28:11,279
One day you will be King and you will understand.

921
01:28:11,849 --> 01:28:15,204
I cannot risk the fate of this quest for the sake of one dwarf.

922
01:28:16,130 --> 01:28:18,331
Not even my own kin.

923
01:28:21,864 --> 01:28:25,224
Fili, don't be a fool. You belong with the company.

924
01:28:25,224 --> 01:28:26,474
I belong with my brother.

925
01:28:38,414 --> 01:28:41,942
By my beard! Is that the time!

926
01:28:43,227 --> 01:28:46,375
Go now with our good will.

927
01:28:48,558 --> 01:28:54,236
- and may your return bring fortune to all! - Wait!

928
01:28:58,080 --> 01:28:59,634
Goodbye!

929
01:29:14,940 --> 01:29:16,823
Did you miss the boat as well?

930
01:29:16,823 --> 01:29:18,023
Kili? Kili!

931
01:29:21,533 --> 01:29:25,033
No. I am done with dwarves. Go away!

932
01:29:25,378 --> 01:29:26,850
No, no. Please!

933
01:29:26,885 --> 01:29:28,938
No one will help us. Kili is sick.

934
01:29:31,568 --> 01:29:33,474
He is very sick.

935
01:30:13,399 --> 01:30:15,329
What is this place?

936
01:30:15,329 --> 01:30:17,604
It was once the city of Dale.

937
01:30:18,591 --> 01:30:20,121
Now, it is a ruin.

938
01:30:21,020 --> 01:30:25,407
- The Desolation of Smaug.  - The sun will soon reached mid-day.

939
01:30:25,407 --> 01:30:28,326
We must find the hidden door into the mountain before it sets.

940
01:30:28,326 --> 01:30:31,234
- This way!  - Wait. Is this... the overlook?

941
01:30:31,434 --> 01:30:35,268
- Gandalf said to meet him here, on no account were we to...  - Do you see him?

942
01:30:35,268 --> 01:30:37,697
We have no time to wait on our wizard.

943
01:30:37,897 --> 01:30:39,780
We are on our own. Come!

944
01:30:56,774 --> 01:30:58,945
Dol Guldur.

945
01:30:58,945 --> 01:31:01,248
The hill of sorcerer.

946
01:31:01,248 --> 01:31:03,607
It looks completely abandoned.

947
01:31:03,607 --> 01:31:05,651
As it is meant to.

948
01:31:06,388 --> 01:31:09,958
A spell of concealment lies over this place.

949
01:31:10,158 --> 01:31:13,967
Which means our Enemy is not yet ready to reveal himself.

950
01:31:16,179 --> 01:31:20,308
He has not regained his full strength.

951
01:31:20,308 --> 01:31:23,552
Radagast, I need you to carry a message to Lady Galadriel.

952
01:31:23,552 --> 01:31:26,143
Tell her, we must force his hand.

953
01:31:26,343 --> 01:31:28,716
- What do you mean?  - I am going in alone.

954
01:31:29,294 --> 01:31:31,835
On no account come after me.

955
01:31:37,722 --> 01:31:41,532
- Do I have your word?  - Yes, yes... yes.

956
01:31:53,362 --> 01:31:55,060
Wait Gandalf!

957
01:31:56,060 --> 01:31:57,955
What if it's a trap?

958
01:31:58,845 --> 01:32:00,718
Turn around...

959
01:32:00,753 --> 01:32:03,393
and do not come back.

960
01:32:07,540 --> 01:32:11,187
It's undoubtedly a trap.

961
01:32:44,583 --> 01:32:47,942


962
01:32:48,885 --> 01:32:51,385


963
01:32:52,487 --> 01:32:55,123


964
01:33:10,059 --> 01:33:13,721
<i>Ce na ulco sis nurtaina...</i>

965
01:33:13,721 --> 01:33:16,772
<i>I ettuluvas caninye!</i>

966
01:33:16,851 --> 01:33:19,303


967
01:33:19,684 --> 01:33:21,555


968
01:33:21,925 --> 01:33:23,255


969
01:33:23,757 --> 01:33:26,519


970
01:33:33,321 --> 01:33:35,728
- Anything?!  - Nothing!

971
01:33:39,689 --> 01:33:43,899
If the map is true, the hidden door lies directly above us.

972
01:33:48,876 --> 01:33:50,503
Up here!

973
01:33:58,683 --> 01:34:01,526
You have keen eyes, Master Baggins.

974
01:34:33,039 --> 01:34:34,131
This must be it.

975
01:34:36,318 --> 01:34:37,774
The hidden door.

976
01:34:42,029 --> 01:34:46,710
Let all those who doubted us, rue this day!

977
01:34:52,019 --> 01:34:54,672
Hey, we have a key.

978
01:34:56,284 --> 01:35:00,253
Which means, there'is somewhere there is a key hole.

979
01:35:01,006 --> 01:35:04,389
The last light of Durin's day...

980
01:35:05,771 --> 01:35:07,722
will shine upon the keyhole.

981
01:35:17,428 --> 01:35:18,490
- Nori.  - Yeah.

982
01:35:25,318 --> 01:35:27,176
We are losing the light, come on!

983
01:35:33,717 --> 01:35:36,334
Be quiet. I can't hear when you're thumping!

984
01:35:36,334 --> 01:35:37,347
I can't find it!

985
01:35:38,964 --> 01:35:41,707
It's not here! It's not here!

986
01:35:43,049 --> 01:35:44,206
Break it down!

987
01:35:46,407 --> 01:35:47,654
Come on!

988
01:35:50,537 --> 01:35:51,940
We lost the light.

989
01:35:52,473 --> 01:35:53,642
It's no good!

990
01:35:53,642 --> 01:35:56,955
The door is sealed. It can't be opened by force!

991
01:35:58,025 --> 01:35:59,705
Powerful magic on it.

992
01:36:08,950 --> 01:36:10,044
No!

993
01:36:15,354 --> 01:36:17,755
"The last light of Durin's day,

994
01:36:19,335 --> 01:36:20,858
will shine upon the keyhole."

995
01:36:25,622 --> 01:36:27,995
That is what it says.

996
01:36:31,474 --> 01:36:33,181
What did we miss?

997
01:36:36,614 --> 01:36:39,003
What did we miss?

998
01:36:39,203 --> 01:36:40,203
Balin?

999
01:36:40,938 --> 01:36:42,690
We have lost the light.

1000
01:36:44,889 --> 01:36:47,727
There is no more to be done.

1001
01:36:48,401 --> 01:36:50,136
We had but one chance.

1002
01:36:53,109 --> 01:36:56,116
Come away, lads. Let's move on.

1003
01:36:57,221 --> 01:36:58,631
Wait a minute. What...

1004
01:37:01,967 --> 01:37:03,213
Where are they going?

1005
01:37:05,225 --> 01:37:07,386
You can't give up now!

1006
01:37:21,867 --> 01:37:23,357
Thorin...

1007
01:37:25,195 --> 01:37:27,329
you can't give up now.

1008
01:37:38,375 --> 01:37:44,696
Stand by the grey stone when the thrush knocks.

1009
01:37:45,461 --> 01:37:47,332
The setting sun...

1010
01:37:48,471 --> 01:37:50,786
and the last light of Durin's day will shine.

1011
01:37:52,511 --> 01:37:54,113
The last light...

1012
01:37:56,504 --> 01:37:58,121
Last light.

1013
01:38:34,314 --> 01:38:35,740
And the last light!

1014
01:38:45,964 --> 01:38:47,020
The keyhole!

1015
01:38:47,675 --> 01:38:50,100
Come back! Come back!

1016
01:38:50,100 --> 01:38:54,896
It is the light of the moon. The last moon of autumn!

1017
01:38:58,131 --> 01:39:00,202
Where is the key? Where is the...

1018
01:39:02,738 --> 01:39:04,334
It was... it was here.

1019
01:39:04,780 --> 01:39:06,293
It was... just...

1020
01:40:03,831 --> 01:40:05,361
Erebor!

1021
01:40:06,097 --> 01:40:07,969
Thorin.

1022
01:40:20,498 --> 01:40:22,813
I know these walls.

1023
01:40:26,220 --> 01:40:28,610
These walls...

1024
01:40:30,591 --> 01:40:32,874
this stone.

1025
01:40:36,232 --> 01:40:38,418
You remember it, Balin?

1026
01:40:41,655 --> 01:40:44,183
Chambers filled with golden light.

1027
01:40:45,950 --> 01:40:48,058
I remember.

1028
01:41:00,863 --> 01:41:05,935
Here in lies the seventh kingdom of Durin's folk.

1029
01:41:07,626 --> 01:41:15,014
May the heart of the mountain unite all dwarves in defense of this home.

1030
01:41:16,231 --> 01:41:18,231
The throne of King.

1031
01:41:22,133 --> 01:41:25,009
And what's that above it?

1032
01:41:28,733 --> 01:41:31,016
The Arkenstone.

1033
01:41:31,935 --> 01:41:33,473
Arkenstone.

1034
01:41:37,104 --> 01:41:38,917
And what's that?

1035
01:41:38,917 --> 01:41:44,288
That, Master Burglar, is why you are here.

1036
01:42:03,612 --> 01:42:05,281
Can you not do something?

1037
01:42:05,281 --> 01:42:07,919
I need herbs. Something to bring down this fever.

1038
01:42:08,194 --> 01:42:10,847
I have nightshade, feverfew...

1039
01:42:10,847 --> 01:42:13,374
They are no use to me. Do you have any kingsfoil?

1040
01:42:13,374 --> 01:42:16,219
No... It's a weed. We feed it to the pigs.

1041
01:42:16,419 --> 01:42:20,486
Pigs? Weed... right.

1042
01:42:21,454 --> 01:42:22,545
Don't move.

1043
01:42:25,283 --> 01:42:29,306
You want me... to find the jewel?

1044
01:42:30,768 --> 01:42:33,642
A large white jewel. Yes!

1045
01:42:35,751 --> 01:42:38,356
That's it? Only... I imagine there's quite a few down there.

1046
01:42:38,356 --> 01:42:42,043
There is only one Arkenstone.

1047
01:42:42,243 --> 01:42:43,897
You will know it when you see it.

1048
01:42:45,513 --> 01:42:46,490
Right.

1049
01:42:50,355 --> 01:42:52,222
In truth lad...

1050
01:42:52,422 --> 01:42:57,116
I... do not know what you will find down there.

1051
01:42:59,299 --> 01:43:02,434
You needn't go if you don't want to. There's no dishonor in turning back.

1052
01:43:02,434 --> 01:43:04,312
No... Balin!

1053
01:43:05,052 --> 01:43:07,067
I promised I would do this.

1054
01:43:07,633 --> 01:43:09,280
And I think I must try.

1055
01:43:14,150 --> 01:43:16,959
- It never ceases to amaze me.  - What's that?

1056
01:43:16,959 --> 01:43:18,886
The courage of hobbits.

1057
01:43:21,058 --> 01:43:26,715
Go now, with as much luck... as you can muster.

1058
01:43:34,830 --> 01:43:36,653
Bilbo...

1059
01:43:37,563 --> 01:43:40,905
if there in fact...

1060
01:43:41,629 --> 01:43:44,750
a live dragon down there,

1061
01:43:46,548 --> 01:43:49,165
don't waken it.

1062
01:44:30,952 --> 01:44:34,980
<i>Ce na ulco sis nurtaina...</i>

1063
01:44:35,946 --> 01:44:38,999
<i>I ettuluvas caninye!</i>

1064
01:44:39,922 --> 01:44:44,524
<i>Canin i sa tanuvaxe!</i>

1065
01:44:56,695 --> 01:45:00,946


1066
01:45:01,718 --> 01:45:03,589


1067
01:45:05,821 --> 01:45:07,395
Where is your master?

1068
01:45:08,973 --> 01:45:10,041
Where is he?

1069
01:45:10,886 --> 01:45:13,493


1070
01:45:14,529 --> 01:45:17,227


1071
01:45:30,686 --> 01:45:32,710


