01:45:38,600 --> 01:45:40,031


1073
01:45:57,883 --> 01:46:00,081


1074
01:46:01,908 --> 01:46:05,509


1075
01:47:23,677 --> 01:47:26,422
Sauron.

1076
01:47:49,060 --> 01:47:50,358
Hello.

1077
01:48:09,017 --> 01:48:10,232
He's not at home.

1078
01:48:11,727 --> 01:48:13,040
Not at home.

1079
01:48:14,056 --> 01:48:15,237
Good.

1080
01:48:16,927 --> 01:48:19,097
Good, good, good.

1081
01:49:13,086 --> 01:49:14,166
What's that?

1082
01:49:20,769 --> 01:49:22,312
Arkenstone.

1083
01:49:23,095 --> 01:49:24,612
Arkenstone.

1084
01:49:25,267 --> 01:49:27,935
A large... white jewel.

1085
01:49:29,481 --> 01:49:30,518
Very helpful.

1086
01:51:56,578 --> 01:51:58,991
Well..

1087
01:51:59,682 --> 01:52:01,343
Thief!

1088
01:52:02,911 --> 01:52:07,098
I... smell... you.

1089
01:52:07,098 --> 01:52:10,691
I hear your breath.

1090
01:52:11,423 --> 01:52:16,004
I feel your air.

1091
01:52:18,259 --> 01:52:21,642
Where are... you.

1092
01:52:21,842 --> 01:52:24,411
Where are you?

1093
01:52:43,339 --> 01:52:47,441
Come now... Don't be shy.

1094
01:52:47,441 --> 01:52:50,742
Step into the light.

1095
01:52:54,179 --> 01:52:55,830
Hhmmm...

1096
01:52:56,576 --> 01:53:01,158
There is... something about you.

1097
01:53:03,242 --> 01:53:06,002
Something you carry.

1098
01:53:06,304 --> 01:53:09,075
Something made of gold.

1099
01:53:09,380 --> 01:53:14,855
But far more... precious!

1100
01:53:20,200 --> 01:53:21,710
There you there,

1101
01:53:21,710 --> 01:53:24,729
thief in the shadows.

1102
01:53:27,185 --> 01:53:29,658
I did not come to steal from you.

1103
01:53:29,858 --> 01:53:33,646
Oh Smaug, the unaccessibly wealthy.

1104
01:53:33,646 --> 01:53:36,535
I merely wanted to gaze upon your magnificence,

1105
01:53:36,535 --> 01:53:40,560
to see if you really were as great as the old tales say.

1106
01:53:40,932 --> 01:53:42,637
I did not believe them.

1107
01:53:51,912 --> 01:53:56,423
And, Do you now?!

1108
01:53:57,177 --> 01:53:58,684
Truly.

1109
01:53:59,523 --> 01:54:02,787
The tales and songs,

1110
01:54:02,787 --> 01:54:07,443
fall utterly short of your enormity, oh Smaug...

1111
01:54:07,443 --> 01:54:08,889
the Stupendous.

1112
01:54:08,889 --> 01:54:12,225
Do you think flattery will keep you alive?

1113
01:54:12,754 --> 01:54:15,214
- No... no.  - No, indeed.

1114
01:54:17,915 --> 01:54:24,945
You seem familiar with my name, but I don't remember smelling your kind before.

1115
01:54:25,145 --> 01:54:29,402
Who are you and where do you come from?

1116
01:54:29,402 --> 01:54:31,893
May I ask?

1117
01:54:41,266 --> 01:54:45,331
- I come from under the hill.  - Under hill?

1118
01:54:48,385 --> 01:54:52,230
And under hills and over hills my path has led.

1119
01:54:52,801 --> 01:54:54,237
And... and

1120
01:54:54,237 --> 01:54:56,574
through the air, I am he who walks unseen.

1121
01:54:56,881 --> 01:54:58,478
Impressive.

1122
01:54:58,678 --> 01:55:01,832
What else do you claim to be?

1123
01:55:01,832 --> 01:55:02,549
I am...

1124
01:55:05,822 --> 01:55:07,545
Luck wearer...

1125
01:55:09,189 --> 01:55:13,482
- Riddle, riddle maker.  - Lovely titles, go on.

1126
01:55:14,085 --> 01:55:20,034
- Barrel rider.  - Barrels. Now that is interesting.

1127
01:55:20,234 --> 01:55:25,076
Then what about your little dwarve friends?

1128
01:55:25,076 --> 01:55:27,806
Where are they hiding?

1129
01:55:28,630 --> 01:55:31,437
Da... dwarves?

1130
01:55:31,867 --> 01:55:36,444
No. No, no. No dwarves here. You've got that all wrong.

1131
01:55:36,444 --> 01:55:41,080
I don't think so, barrel rider.

1132
01:55:41,080 --> 01:55:47,295
They sent you in here to do their dirty work while they skulk about outside.

1133
01:55:47,908 --> 01:55:54,674
Truly, you are mistaken, oh Smaug, chiefest and greatest of calamities.

1134
01:55:55,080 --> 01:56:01,200
You have nice manners for a thief and a liar.

1135
01:56:02,556 --> 01:56:06,574
I know the smell and taste of Dwarf.

1136
01:56:06,574 --> 01:56:08,586
No one better.

1137
01:56:09,060 --> 01:56:10,677
It is the gold,

1138
01:56:10,877 --> 01:56:16,272
they are drawn to treasure like flies to dead flesh.

1139
01:56:18,585 --> 01:56:22,016
Did you think I did not know this day would come?

1140
01:56:23,427 --> 01:56:31,068
That a pack of canting dwarves would come crawling back to the mountain?

1141
01:56:35,001 --> 01:56:38,862
- Was that an earthquake?  - That, my lad...

1142
01:56:41,993 --> 01:56:43,717
was a dragon.

1143
01:56:52,068 --> 01:56:54,486
- Da?  - It's coming from the mountain.

1144
01:56:58,593 --> 01:57:02,222
You should leave us. Take your children, get out of here.

1145
01:57:02,422 --> 01:57:03,722
And go where?

1146
01:57:04,852 --> 01:57:06,817
There is no where to go.

1147
01:57:08,276 --> 01:57:10,441
Are we going to die, Da?

1148
01:57:12,044 --> 01:57:13,133
No, darling.

1149
01:57:13,133 --> 01:57:15,549
The dragon, it's going to kill us.

1150
01:57:26,153 --> 01:57:28,722
Not if I kill it first.

1151
01:57:29,701 --> 01:57:33,388
The king under the mountain is dead.

1152
01:57:33,388 --> 01:57:39,834
I took his throne, I ate his people... like a wolf among sheep.

1153
01:57:42,951 --> 01:57:48,188
I kill where I wish, when I wish.

1154
01:57:48,188 --> 01:57:51,773
My armour is iron!

1155
01:57:59,884 --> 01:58:03,257
No blade can pierce me!

1156
01:58:06,237 --> 01:58:07,089
Alright.

1157
01:58:07,505 --> 01:58:10,373
A Black Arrow. Why did you never tell me?

1158
01:58:10,373 --> 01:58:12,026
Because you did not need to know.

1159
01:58:19,597 --> 01:58:23,262
Listen to me carefully, I need you to distract the guards.

1160
01:58:24,126 --> 01:58:27,455
Once I'm at the top of the tower, I'll slip the arrow to the bow.

1161
01:58:27,455 --> 01:58:29,824
There he is! Guards, after him!

1162
01:58:29,824 --> 01:58:32,766
- Quickly! Down there! Go!  - Stop him!

1163
01:58:39,681 --> 01:58:40,415
Stop him!

1164
01:58:48,587 --> 01:58:51,699
- Keep it safe. Don't let anyone find  - No!

1165
01:58:51,699 --> 01:58:54,680
- I'll deal with them. Now, go!  - I can't leave you!

1166
01:58:58,086 --> 01:58:59,916
- Braga?  - You are under arrest.

1167
01:58:59,916 --> 01:59:03,231
- On what charge?  - Any charge the Master chooses.

1168
01:59:45,210 --> 01:59:48,135
- What about Bilbo?  - Give him more time.

1169
01:59:48,335 --> 01:59:51,008
Time to do what? To be killed?

1170
01:59:52,701 --> 01:59:53,950
You are afraid?

1171
01:59:55,657 --> 01:59:58,291
Yes... I'm afraid.

1172
01:59:59,161 --> 02:00:01,818
I fear for you.

1173
02:00:01,818 --> 02:00:04,261
A sickness lies upon that treasure hoard.

1174
02:00:04,261 --> 02:00:06,751
A sickness which drove your granfather mad!

1175
02:00:06,751 --> 02:00:10,096
- I am not my grandfather.  - You're not yourself!

1176
02:00:11,366 --> 02:00:15,228
- The Thorin I know would not hesitate to go in there.  - I will not risk this quest...

1177
02:00:15,228 --> 02:00:18,435
for the life of one, burglar.

1178
02:00:20,430 --> 02:00:24,080
Bilbo... His name is Bilbo.

1179
02:00:27,126 --> 02:00:33,027
It's Oakenshield... That filthy dwarvish usurper...

1180
02:00:35,075 --> 02:00:40,458
He sent you in here for the Arkenstone... Didn't he?

1181
02:00:40,458 --> 02:00:41,979
No! No... no.

1182
02:00:41,979 --> 02:00:44,385
I don't know what you're talking about.

1183
02:00:44,585 --> 02:00:46,521
Don't bother denying it.

1184
02:00:46,521 --> 02:00:49,774
I guessed his foul purpose some time ago.

1185
02:00:51,259 --> 02:00:57,531
But it matters not. Oakenshield's quest will fail.

1186
02:00:58,567 --> 02:01:04,896
A darkness is coming. It will spread to every corner of the land!

1187
02:01:35,862 --> 02:01:39,910
<i>The filthy dwarf rats are somewhere here.</i>

1188
02:01:40,478 --> 02:01:43,203
<i>I can smell them.</i>

1189
02:01:47,818 --> 02:01:51,053
You have been used, thief in the shadow.

1190
02:01:51,053 --> 02:01:54,937
You were only ever a means to an end.

1191
02:01:55,733 --> 02:02:01,922
The coward Oakenshield has weighed the value of your life and found...

1192
02:02:01,922 --> 02:02:03,957
it worth nothing!

1193
02:02:03,957 --> 02:02:06,610
No. No.

1194
02:02:07,960 --> 02:02:10,922
- No, you're lying.  - What did he promise you?

1195
02:02:10,922 --> 02:02:13,216
A share of his treasure?

1196
02:02:13,967 --> 02:02:16,253
As if it were his to give.

1197
02:02:17,123 --> 02:02:23,585
I would not part with a single coin. Not one piece of it!

1198
02:02:27,242 --> 02:02:30,251
My teeths are swords!

1199
02:02:30,451 --> 02:02:33,895
My claws are spears!

1200
02:02:35,972 --> 02:02:41,064
My wings... are a hurricane!

1201
02:02:45,960 --> 02:02:47,518
So, it is true.

1202
02:02:48,106 --> 02:02:50,183
The black arrow found its mark.

1203
02:02:50,183 --> 02:02:53,386
- What did you say?  - I was just saying...

1204
02:02:53,386 --> 02:02:54,879
your reputation preceeds you.

1205
02:02:55,180 --> 02:02:57,648
Oh Smaug, the tyrannical...

1206
02:02:58,003 --> 02:03:02,787
truly, you have no equal on this earth.

1207
02:03:05,993 --> 02:03:10,165
I am almost tempted to let you take it,

1208
02:03:10,165 --> 02:03:14,237
if only to see Oakenshield suffer.

1209
02:03:14,905 --> 02:03:21,155
Watch it destroy him. Watch it corrupt his heart...

1210
02:03:21,155 --> 02:03:24,228
and drive him mad!

1211
02:03:27,560 --> 02:03:31,919
But I think not, I think our little game ends here.

1212
02:03:32,677 --> 02:03:38,773
So tell me, thief. How do you choose to die?

1213
02:04:26,883 --> 02:04:28,243
<i>Dwarves!</i>

1214
02:04:50,715 --> 02:04:52,798
Da? Is that you, Da?

1215
02:06:40,889 --> 02:06:43,088


1216
02:06:44,147 --> 02:06:45,127


1217
02:06:45,525 --> 02:06:46,820


1218
02:07:05,422 --> 02:07:07,577
- You've killed them all.  - There are others.

1219
02:07:08,276 --> 02:07:09,504
Tauriel, go.

1220
02:07:14,915 --> 02:07:17,404
We are losing him!

1221
02:07:19,884 --> 02:07:20,903
Tauriel?

1222
02:07:44,743 --> 02:07:45,877
<i>Athelas!</i>

1223
02:07:48,826 --> 02:07:50,575
<i>Athelas...</i>

1224
02:07:51,104 --> 02:07:52,957
What are you doing?

1225
02:07:55,064 --> 02:07:57,405
I'm going to save him.

1226
02:08:17,939 --> 02:08:19,237
- You are alive!  - Not for much longer!

1227
02:08:19,237 --> 02:08:21,115
- Did you find the Arkenstone?  - The dragon's coming!

1228
02:08:21,115 --> 02:08:22,925
The Arkenstone?

1229
02:08:25,303 --> 02:08:26,930
Did you find it?

1230
02:08:32,347 --> 02:08:33,727
No. We have to get out.

1231
02:08:37,021 --> 02:08:38,501
Thorin?

1232
02:08:41,751 --> 02:08:43,310
Thorin!

1233
02:09:13,408 --> 02:09:16,447
You will burn!

1234
02:09:24,573 --> 02:09:25,703
Come on, Bilbo!

1235
02:09:38,680 --> 02:09:39,711
Come on.

1236
02:09:56,744 --> 02:09:58,135
Hold him down.

1237
02:10:06,774 --> 02:10:10,486
<i>May the blessing that was given to me be sent from me to him,</i>

1238
02:10:10,704 --> 02:10:13,150
<i>may he be released from death.</i>

1239
02:10:15,057 --> 02:10:16,079
Tilda!

1240
02:10:16,864 --> 02:10:20,752
<i>May the blessing that was given to me be sent from me to him,</i>

1241
02:10:20,752 --> 02:10:22,464
<i>may he be released from death.</i>

1242
02:10:22,823 --> 02:10:26,995
<i>May the blessing that was given to me be sent from me to him,</i>

1243
02:10:26,995 --> 02:10:28,758
<i>may he be released from death.</i>

1244
02:10:28,758 --> 02:10:33,161
<i>May the blessing that was given to me be sent from me to him,</i>

1245
02:10:33,161 --> 02:10:35,225
<i>may he be released from death.</i>

1246
02:10:35,929 --> 02:10:42,034
<i>May the blessing that was given to me be sent from me to him,</i>

1247
02:10:43,519 --> 02:10:46,564
<i>may he be released from death.</i>

1248
02:11:08,992 --> 02:11:10,191
Ssh. Ssh-ssh.

1249
02:11:18,138 --> 02:11:23,177
- We've given him the slip.  - No. He is too cunning for that.

1250
02:11:24,994 --> 02:11:28,212
- So, where to now?  - The western guard room.

1251
02:11:28,865 --> 02:11:30,192
There may be a way out.

1252
02:11:30,758 --> 02:11:34,812
- It's too high, there's no chance that way.  - It's our only chance.

1253
02:11:36,426 --> 02:11:37,898
We have to try.

1254
02:11:54,486 --> 02:11:55,696
Come on.

1255
02:12:43,235 --> 02:12:46,752
I've heard tales of the wonders of elvish medicine.

1256
02:12:47,128 --> 02:12:49,782
That was a privelege to witness.

1257
02:12:52,263 --> 02:12:53,444
Tauriel.

1258
02:12:57,596 --> 02:12:58,964
Lie still.

1259
02:13:06,229 --> 02:13:08,250
You cannot be her.

1260
02:13:11,812 --> 02:13:13,887
She is far away.

1261
02:13:15,891 --> 02:13:22,140
She... she is far, far away from me.

1262
02:13:23,022 --> 02:13:25,553
She walks...

1263
02:13:25,553 --> 02:13:29,540
under the stars in another world.

1264
02:13:33,494 --> 02:13:35,505
It was just a dream.

1265
02:13:47,261 --> 02:13:50,343
Do you think she could've loved me?

1266
02:13:56,769 --> 02:13:57,974
Stay close.

1267
02:14:07,999 --> 02:14:11,799
That's it then. There's no way out.

1268
02:14:18,290 --> 02:14:20,363
The last of our kin.

1269
02:14:24,301 --> 02:14:26,733
They must have come here...

1270
02:14:26,733 --> 02:14:30,136
hoping beyond hope.

1271
02:14:39,121 --> 02:14:41,397
We could try to reach the mines.

1272
02:14:42,510 --> 02:14:44,278
My last few days.

1273
02:14:46,536 --> 02:14:48,065
No.

1274
02:14:50,913 --> 02:14:53,351
I will not die like this.

1275
02:14:54,468 --> 02:14:58,005
Cowering... clawing for breath.

1276
02:15:03,003 --> 02:15:06,418
- We make for the forges.  - He'll see us, sure as death.

1277
02:15:06,418 --> 02:15:08,057
Not if we split up.

1278
02:15:08,057 --> 02:15:11,028
Thorin, we will never make it.

1279
02:15:11,228 --> 02:15:12,590
Some of us might.

1280
02:15:13,124 --> 02:15:15,732
Lead him to the forges.

1281
02:15:16,155 --> 02:15:19,427
We kill the dragon.

1282
02:15:19,824 --> 02:15:24,452
If this is to end in fire, then we will all burn together.

1283
02:15:26,132 --> 02:15:27,314
This way!

1284
02:15:32,173 --> 02:15:35,144
Flee! Flee!

1285
02:15:35,344 --> 02:15:38,233
Run for your lives!

1286
02:15:38,233 --> 02:15:43,514
- There is nowhere to hide.  - Behind you!

1287
02:15:53,039 --> 02:15:54,753
Here!

1288
02:16:25,992 --> 02:16:28,539


1289
02:16:28,903 --> 02:16:31,698


1290
02:16:42,550 --> 02:16:43,518


1291
02:16:44,292 --> 02:16:46,281


1292
02:18:51,768 --> 02:18:53,851
This way! It's this way!

1293
02:18:53,851 --> 02:18:55,540
Come on!

1294
02:18:55,540 --> 02:18:57,031
Thorin!

1295
02:19:01,626 --> 02:19:02,718
Follow Balin!

1296
02:19:04,570 --> 02:19:05,604
Come on!

1297
02:19:21,075 --> 02:19:22,305
Thorin!

1298
02:19:31,645 --> 02:19:33,331
Hold on!

1299
02:20:10,456 --> 02:20:11,992
Go! Go!

1300
02:20:15,934 --> 02:20:19,841
The plan's not gonna work! These furnaces are stone cold.

1301
02:20:19,841 --> 02:20:23,678
He is right. We've no fire hot enough to set them ablaze.

1302
02:20:26,249 --> 02:20:28,046
Have we not.

1303
02:20:29,175 --> 02:20:31,909
I did not look to see you so easily outwitted!

1304
02:20:36,151 --> 02:20:39,161
You are growing slow and fat...

1305
02:20:40,116 --> 02:20:42,493
in your dotage.

1306
02:20:42,493 --> 02:20:44,625
Slug!

1307
02:20:45,765 --> 02:20:47,810
Take cover. Go!

1308
02:21:14,757 --> 02:21:17,829
Bombur! Get those billows working! Go!

1309
02:21:32,381 --> 02:21:34,364
Bilbo! Up there.

1310
02:21:34,364 --> 02:21:36,490
On my mark, pull that lever.

1311
02:21:46,957 --> 02:21:49,415
Balin, can you still mix a flash flame?

1312
02:21:49,415 --> 02:21:51,285
Aye, it will only take a jiffy!

1313
02:21:51,285 --> 02:21:52,285
Come on!

1314
02:21:53,651 --> 02:21:55,032
We don't have a jiffy.

1315
02:22:06,955 --> 02:22:08,462
Where's the sulfur?

1316
02:22:08,462 --> 02:22:10,187
Are you sure you know what you're doing?

1317
02:22:22,138 --> 02:22:23,534
Come on!

1318
02:22:45,119 --> 02:22:46,314
Now!

1319
02:24:42,666 --> 02:24:44,589
Lead him to the Gallery of the Kings.

1320
02:25:32,593 --> 02:25:34,896
Keep going, Bilbo! Run!

1321
02:26:20,702 --> 02:26:25,962
You think you can deceive me, barrel rider?

1322
02:26:27,510 --> 02:26:30,382
You have come from Lake-town.

1323
02:26:31,795 --> 02:26:37,387
This is some sordid scheme hatched between these filthy dwarves...

1324
02:26:37,387 --> 02:26:40,057
and those miserable tarp trading lakemen.

1325
02:26:41,188 --> 02:26:47,519
Those sniveling cowards with their long bows and black arrows.

1326
02:26:48,161 --> 02:26:53,275
Perhaps it is time I pay them a visit. 

1327
02:26:53,316 --> 02:26:54,157
No.

1328
02:26:56,160 --> 02:26:57,889
This isn't their fault.

1329
02:26:57,889 --> 02:27:00,689
Wait! You cannot go to Lake-town.

1330
02:27:02,505 --> 02:27:06,555
You care about them, do you?

1331
02:27:07,037 --> 02:27:11,866
Good. Then you could watch them die!

